WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.449 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.449 --> 00:00:13.419 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:13.419 --> 00:00:27.350 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.350 --> 00:00:31.800 align:middle line:10%
GESAR MUKPO: In 1900, a
child was born in Tibet.

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:33.770 align:middle line:84%
He would become a
great Buddhist master.

00:00:33.770 --> 00:00:40.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:43.190 align:middle line:84%
His name was Shechen
Kongtrul Rinpoche.

00:00:43.190 --> 00:00:47.360 align:middle line:90%


00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:50.200 align:middle line:84%
In 1960, he died
while imprisoned

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:51.390 align:middle line:90%
by the Chinese government.

00:00:51.390 --> 00:00:55.380 align:middle line:90%


00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:02.745 align:middle line:84%
In 1973, he would be
reborn in America as me.

00:01:02.745 --> 00:01:42.624 align:middle line:90%


00:01:42.624 --> 00:01:46.800 align:middle line:90%
[RAP MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:56.300 align:middle line:90%


00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:58.244 align:middle line:84%
MAN: How many
tracks will it play?

00:01:58.244 --> 00:01:59.110 align:middle line:90%
GESAR MUKPO: I don't know.

00:01:59.110 --> 00:02:01.210 align:middle line:90%
It seems fine with six.

00:02:01.210 --> 00:02:02.620 align:middle line:90%
So say I'll take just this one.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:05.560 align:middle line:84%
And I know that's like one
of the ones I want to use.

00:02:05.560 --> 00:02:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And then lay that one
down so that I can put

00:02:08.560 --> 00:02:09.590 align:middle line:90%
the other ones on top of that.

00:02:09.590 --> 00:02:10.890 align:middle line:84%
So we've got this
one for this section.

00:02:10.890 --> 00:02:12.357 align:middle line:84%
This one's my main one
for the next section.

00:02:12.357 --> 00:02:13.856 align:middle line:84%
This one is my main one
for the next section.

00:02:13.856 --> 00:02:15.367 align:middle line:84%
This one is my main one
for the next section.

00:02:15.367 --> 00:02:16.708 align:middle line:84%
Or you can take
them if you want.

00:02:16.708 --> 00:02:18.050 align:middle line:90%
Or I can take them.

00:02:18.050 --> 00:02:19.800 align:middle line:84%
If you're thinking I don't
look like an enlightened

00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:22.100 align:middle line:90%
Buddhist master, you're right.

00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:24.675 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't think of a worse
way to describe myself.

00:02:24.675 --> 00:02:26.445 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, exactly, that's
what Tibetans--

00:02:26.445 --> 00:02:29.510 align:middle line:84%
I think I told you that
Shechen, they do this hot water

00:02:29.510 --> 00:02:30.496 align:middle line:90%
with milk and honey.

00:02:30.496 --> 00:02:31.460 align:middle line:90%
Papa.

00:02:31.460 --> 00:02:33.272 align:middle line:90%
Papa?

00:02:33.272 --> 00:02:34.480 align:middle line:90%
Papa!

00:02:34.480 --> 00:02:35.572 align:middle line:90%
I drink tea.

00:02:35.572 --> 00:02:37.110 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you do.
You should drink it.

00:02:37.110 --> 00:02:39.540 align:middle line:84%
Then you can go to Tibet
and have tea there.

00:02:39.540 --> 00:02:41.680 align:middle line:84%
Other than the fact that
I make music videos,

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:44.420 align:middle line:90%
my life is pretty ordinary.

00:02:44.420 --> 00:02:45.790 align:middle line:84%
I struggle with the
responsibilities

00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:47.250 align:middle line:90%
of being a parent.

00:02:47.250 --> 00:02:48.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm separated from my wife.

00:02:48.930 --> 00:02:50.425 align:middle line:84%
And I live from
paycheck to paycheck.

00:02:50.425 --> 00:02:53.024 align:middle line:90%


00:02:53.024 --> 00:02:54.290 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to see
you tomorrow, honey.

00:02:54.290 --> 00:02:56.154 align:middle line:90%
Let's give me a hug.

00:02:56.154 --> 00:02:58.018 align:middle line:90%
Give me a hug, sweetie.

00:02:58.018 --> 00:02:59.300 align:middle line:90%
Can you say bye?

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:00.195 align:middle line:90%
I'll see you tomorrow.

00:03:00.195 --> 00:03:02.692 align:middle line:84%
You're coming down to my house
tomorrow to feed the fish.

00:03:02.692 --> 00:03:07.552 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:07.552 --> 00:03:17.214 align:middle line:90%


00:03:17.214 --> 00:03:18.880 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: I'm looking
at some of the belongings

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:21.350 align:middle line:90%
of Shechen Kongtrul Rinpoche.

00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:23.820 align:middle line:84%
They were recently delivered
to me by a friend returning

00:03:23.820 --> 00:03:24.830 align:middle line:90%
from a monastery in Nepal.

00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:31.120 align:middle line:90%


00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:33.980 align:middle line:84%
These exquisite paintings were
used in Buddhist initiations

00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:37.590 align:middle line:90%
in Tibet for hundreds of years.

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:40.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, they sit in a box
in my bedroom closet.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:43.663 align:middle line:90%


00:03:43.663 --> 00:03:49.531 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:03:49.531 --> 00:04:02.770 align:middle line:90%


00:04:02.770 --> 00:04:05.260 align:middle line:84%
In the 16th century,
one in four Tibetans

00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:09.050 align:middle line:90%
was Buddhist monk or nun.

00:04:09.050 --> 00:04:11.770 align:middle line:84%
It was during this golden
age of Tibetan Buddhism

00:04:11.770 --> 00:04:14.840 align:middle line:84%
that a tradition originated
whereupon the passing away

00:04:14.840 --> 00:04:16.769 align:middle line:84%
of an enlightened
Buddhist teacher,

00:04:16.769 --> 00:04:17.935 align:middle line:84%
a young child
would be recognized

00:04:17.935 --> 00:04:20.870 align:middle line:90%
as the reincarnation.

00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:22.380 align:middle line:84%
This child would
assume leadership

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:24.470 align:middle line:84%
of their predecessor's
monastery,

00:04:24.470 --> 00:04:27.320 align:middle line:84%
as well as the
surrounding villages.

00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:32.030 align:middle line:84%
They called these
children tulkus.

00:04:32.030 --> 00:04:35.420 align:middle line:84%
Some became great
leaders, others, teachers,

00:04:35.420 --> 00:04:39.720 align:middle line:90%
scholars, poets, and yogis.

00:04:39.720 --> 00:04:43.030 align:middle line:84%
For hundreds of years, this
tradition remained unchanged.

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:47.920 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:53.800 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.800 --> 00:04:57.330 align:middle line:84%
In the 1970s, something
interesting started happening.

00:04:57.330 --> 00:05:00.910 align:middle line:84%
Tulkus were being
discovered in the West.

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:04.220 align:middle line:84%
I know because I was
one of them, recognized

00:05:04.220 --> 00:05:07.630 align:middle line:84%
by Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche,
a revered Buddhist master,

00:05:07.630 --> 00:05:12.440 align:middle line:84%
during his visit to
California in 1976.

00:05:12.440 --> 00:05:14.200 align:middle line:84%
He informed my
family he believed

00:05:14.200 --> 00:05:17.160 align:middle line:84%
I was a tulku, the reincarnation
of one of his peers

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:19.010 align:middle line:84%
who had died in Tibet,
and that I should

00:05:19.010 --> 00:05:19.905 align:middle line:90%
be enthroned immediately.

00:05:19.905 --> 00:05:23.210 align:middle line:90%


00:05:23.210 --> 00:05:26.330 align:middle line:84%
So at three years old, I
was enthrones as a tulku

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:28.040 align:middle line:90%
in Berkeley, California.

00:05:28.040 --> 00:05:34.540 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGING]

00:05:34.540 --> 00:05:35.700 align:middle line:90%
That's where my story begins.

00:05:35.700 --> 00:05:39.886 align:middle line:90%


00:05:39.886 --> 00:05:42.808 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN CHANTING]

00:05:42.808 --> 00:05:51.100 align:middle line:90%


00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:53.620 align:middle line:90%
My name is Gesar Mukpo.

00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And I live in
Halifax, Nova Scotia.

00:05:56.670 --> 00:05:59.240 align:middle line:84%
I've been a constant
traveler, growing up

00:05:59.240 --> 00:06:01.730 align:middle line:84%
in the United States,
Canada, England,

00:06:01.730 --> 00:06:05.790 align:middle line:90%
Germany, and even India.

00:06:05.790 --> 00:06:08.070 align:middle line:84%
But before I tell you
any more about myself,

00:06:08.070 --> 00:06:09.480 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to take a
look at another tulku

00:06:09.480 --> 00:06:11.820 align:middle line:84%
who grew up in
Halifax, a close friend

00:06:11.820 --> 00:06:13.155 align:middle line:90%
of mine, Dylan Henderson.

00:06:13.155 --> 00:06:16.440 align:middle line:90%


00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:18.580 align:middle line:84%
Dylan was the first
Caucasian tulku

00:06:18.580 --> 00:06:20.530 align:middle line:90%
to be discovered in the West.

00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:24.230 align:middle line:84%
He was recognized in
1975 by the great teacher

00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:28.060 align:middle line:84%
and scholar, Chogyam
Trungpa Rinpoche, my father.

00:06:28.060 --> 00:06:42.180 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.180 --> 00:06:45.060 align:middle line:84%
Dylan certainly
has a unique story,

00:06:45.060 --> 00:06:48.240 align:middle line:84%
that of a blond haired,
blue-eyed Western child

00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:51.780 align:middle line:84%
chosen by Tibetan monks as the
reincarnation of their teacher.

00:06:51.780 --> 00:06:55.385 align:middle line:84%
There's paparazzi
over there, OK?

00:06:55.385 --> 00:06:56.674 align:middle line:84%
They're following you.
-Grammy?

00:06:56.674 --> 00:06:58.367 align:middle line:84%
Grammy?
Oh, yes, yes.

00:06:58.367 --> 00:07:01.360 align:middle line:90%


00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:02.590 align:middle line:84%
There's a little
picture over here.

00:07:02.590 --> 00:07:05.091 align:middle line:84%
Is that me or is that
Jen, the Yoda picture?

00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:05.990 align:middle line:90%
DYLAN'S MOTHER: That's you.

00:07:05.990 --> 00:07:08.511 align:middle line:84%
No, you looked like
you were 80 years old.

00:07:08.511 --> 00:07:09.210 align:middle line:90%
You just--

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:10.351 align:middle line:84%
DYLAN HENDERSON: I
had the old man look?

00:07:10.351 --> 00:07:11.050 align:middle line:90%
DYLAN'S MOTHER: Yeah.

00:07:11.050 --> 00:07:13.180 align:middle line:90%


00:07:13.180 --> 00:07:15.614 align:middle line:84%
DYLAN HENDERSON: There's my
father looking like a hippy.

00:07:15.614 --> 00:07:16.480 align:middle line:90%
DYLAN'S MOTHER: Excuse me.

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:18.890 align:middle line:84%
There's your father
looking like you.

00:07:18.890 --> 00:07:20.460 align:middle line:90%
See that green van?

00:07:20.460 --> 00:07:25.540 align:middle line:84%
We lived in that green
van till Dylan was born.

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:28.800 align:middle line:84%
We met at a Jimi
Hendrix concert.

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.330 align:middle line:84%
I was involved with
the anti-war movement.

00:07:31.330 --> 00:07:34.540 align:middle line:84%
I went south and I worked with
Martin Luther King's group

00:07:34.540 --> 00:07:36.740 align:middle line:90%
outside of Atlanta, Georgia.

00:07:36.740 --> 00:07:38.790 align:middle line:90%
And his father was an activist.

00:07:38.790 --> 00:07:40.110 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I didn't even do that.

00:07:40.110 --> 00:07:40.960 align:middle line:90%
Worked my teeth, so--

00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:42.060 align:middle line:84%
DYLAN HENDERSON:
My mother became

00:07:42.060 --> 00:07:44.510 align:middle line:90%
interested in Tibetan Buddhism.

00:07:44.510 --> 00:07:47.860 align:middle line:84%
Summer of '75, went out
to Boulder, Colorado

00:07:47.860 --> 00:07:53.500 align:middle line:84%
to Naropa Institute to do a
program with Trungpa Rinpoche.

00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:55.890 align:middle line:90%
Walked up after a talk.

00:07:55.890 --> 00:08:00.090 align:middle line:84%
Sort of presented myself,
and the next morning-- or

00:08:00.090 --> 00:08:02.584 align:middle line:90%
that night, Rinpoche came back.

00:08:02.584 --> 00:08:03.650 align:middle line:90%
He said, you want to talk to me?

00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:06.750 align:middle line:90%
Be at my office in the morning.

00:08:06.750 --> 00:08:09.920 align:middle line:90%
And we went and met him.

00:08:09.920 --> 00:08:13.840 align:middle line:84%
I pushed ahead of her and ran
into the room to meet Rinpoche.

00:08:13.840 --> 00:08:19.620 align:middle line:84%
And I felt at that time
there was a real connection.

00:08:19.620 --> 00:08:25.170 align:middle line:84%
It was like a loved
one or-- this may

00:08:25.170 --> 00:08:27.300 align:middle line:90%
sound strange, but a parent.

00:08:27.300 --> 00:08:29.180 align:middle line:90%
It had that sense.

00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:31.240 align:middle line:84%
And I felt I didn't
know exactly why

00:08:31.240 --> 00:08:33.400 align:middle line:84%
I was connected to this
person or anything like that.

00:08:33.400 --> 00:08:35.080 align:middle line:90%
But I felt this connection.

00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:38.490 align:middle line:90%


00:08:38.490 --> 00:08:41.150 align:middle line:84%
He had told my mother
and people around.

00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:43.840 align:middle line:84%
But he didn't make
this general knowledge

00:08:43.840 --> 00:08:47.990 align:middle line:90%
that I was one of his teachers.

00:08:47.990 --> 00:08:50.940 align:middle line:90%
But he didn't say who.

00:08:50.940 --> 00:08:52.550 align:middle line:90%
And he left it that.

00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:54.966 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:08:54.966 --> 00:09:00.110 align:middle line:84%
At that point, he wanted me
to go to meet His Holiness

00:09:00.110 --> 00:09:02.500 align:middle line:84%
Karmapa, who was going to
be giving a black crown

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.950 align:middle line:90%
ceremony in Boulder.

00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:06.390 align:middle line:90%
And I met His Holiness Karmapa.

00:09:06.390 --> 00:09:11.340 align:middle line:84%
And I also had a very
strong connection with him.

00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:16.870 align:middle line:84%
And then he confirmed the
recognition of me as a tulku.

00:09:16.870 --> 00:09:20.190 align:middle line:84%
And at that point,
he wanted me to come

00:09:20.190 --> 00:09:24.570 align:middle line:84%
to Rumtek, where I would be
enthroned and put in robes.

00:09:24.570 --> 00:09:27.730 align:middle line:84%
And that would be the
last you ever hear of me.

00:09:27.730 --> 00:09:29.710 align:middle line:90%
But Trungpa Rinpoche said no.

00:09:29.710 --> 00:09:32.970 align:middle line:84%
He said he was born in
the West for a reason.

00:09:32.970 --> 00:09:36.070 align:middle line:84%
And he would undersee
my education.

00:09:36.070 --> 00:09:37.780 align:middle line:84%
And I would not be
taken to Rumtek.

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:41.380 align:middle line:90%


00:09:41.380 --> 00:09:46.770 align:middle line:84%
Whatever I do, I need
to study and practice.

00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:48.680 align:middle line:84%
It's helped me to understand
a lot of the problems

00:09:48.680 --> 00:09:51.030 align:middle line:84%
that I had being a
tulku in the West

00:09:51.030 --> 00:09:54.170 align:middle line:84%
and not having a
form and a structure

00:09:54.170 --> 00:09:55.615 align:middle line:84%
that tulkus maybe
had in the East.

00:09:55.615 --> 00:10:10.120 align:middle line:90%


00:10:10.120 --> 00:10:13.410 align:middle line:84%
I have a degree in
anthropology and history,

00:10:13.410 --> 00:10:14.873 align:middle line:90%
both very fascinating subjects.

00:10:14.873 --> 00:10:19.520 align:middle line:90%


00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:21.700 align:middle line:90%
Diving is wonderful.

00:10:21.700 --> 00:10:23.695 align:middle line:84%
For me, it's taken on a
quality of being a meditation

00:10:23.695 --> 00:10:27.450 align:middle line:84%
in action practice
because it really

00:10:27.450 --> 00:10:29.950 align:middle line:90%
helps me work with my mind.

00:10:29.950 --> 00:10:34.040 align:middle line:84%
I have to really be present and
very aware of my surroundings.

00:10:34.040 --> 00:10:38.450 align:middle line:90%


00:10:38.450 --> 00:10:40.130 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: My father
had made the same decision

00:10:40.130 --> 00:10:42.130 align:middle line:90%
about my education.

00:10:42.130 --> 00:10:46.050 align:middle line:84%
So Dylan and I have had to
ponder the same question.

00:10:46.050 --> 00:10:47.250 align:middle line:84%
If we weren't going
to be brought up

00:10:47.250 --> 00:10:50.330 align:middle line:84%
in the traditional
way in a monastery,

00:10:50.330 --> 00:10:51.800 align:middle line:84%
what does it even
mean to be a tulku?

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:58.670 align:middle line:90%


00:10:58.670 --> 00:11:02.278 align:middle line:84%
WOMAN: Are there any charlatans
teaching at Naropa this summer?

00:11:02.278 --> 00:11:04.668 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:04.668 --> 00:11:08.980 align:middle line:90%


00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:10.700 align:middle line:90%
Well, we have to have someone.

00:11:10.700 --> 00:11:14.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:14.070 --> 00:11:15.620 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise, things too clean.

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:19.556 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:19.556 --> 00:11:23.000 align:middle line:90%


00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.980 align:middle line:84%
And often, some
of the charlatans

00:11:24.980 --> 00:11:31.960 align:middle line:84%
also inspire the students in
the name of being teachers.

00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:34.370 align:middle line:90%
So there's room for that.

00:11:34.370 --> 00:11:35.340 align:middle line:90%
We had to grow up.

00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:40.190 align:middle line:90%


00:11:40.190 --> 00:11:49.270 align:middle line:84%
And it had to become American
Buddhists who inspired

00:11:49.270 --> 00:11:52.500 align:middle line:84%
and who has the
understanding together.

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:54.780 align:middle line:84%
It can only work with
the Western world

00:11:54.780 --> 00:12:01.070 align:middle line:84%
is that it is necessary to
have that kind of situation.

00:12:01.070 --> 00:12:05.350 align:middle line:84%
There is a point at
the level that how far

00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:11.960 align:middle line:90%
we can live on import.

00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:14.050 align:middle line:84%
And there's some
point that we've

00:12:14.050 --> 00:12:17.080 align:middle line:84%
got to manufacture ourselves
rather than borrowing

00:12:17.080 --> 00:12:18.870 align:middle line:90%
from someone else.

00:12:18.870 --> 00:12:20.560 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you owe
an enormous debt.

00:12:20.560 --> 00:12:24.010 align:middle line:90%


00:12:24.010 --> 00:12:26.610 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: My
father died in 1987

00:12:26.610 --> 00:12:30.010 align:middle line:84%
and took with him the answers
to so many of my questions.

00:12:30.010 --> 00:12:34.320 align:middle line:84%
So I head to Florida to see my
mother, hear her recollections,

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:36.240 align:middle line:90%
and get her advice.

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:38.260 align:middle line:84%
DIANA MUKPO: I had a dream
also before you were conceived,

00:12:38.260 --> 00:12:39.950 align:middle line:90%
which was quite interesting.

00:12:39.950 --> 00:12:42.070 align:middle line:84%
I was at Karma Choling
with your father.

00:12:42.070 --> 00:12:45.430 align:middle line:84%
And in my dream, I went
into the room next door.

00:12:45.430 --> 00:12:47.310 align:middle line:84%
And there was a being there,
standing in the corner.

00:12:47.310 --> 00:12:49.330 align:middle line:90%
It was a male being.

00:12:49.330 --> 00:12:53.150 align:middle line:84%
And said to me in the dream,
said, please, will you

00:12:53.150 --> 00:12:55.130 align:middle line:90%
give me a place in your body.

00:12:55.130 --> 00:12:57.250 align:middle line:84%
And I was pregnant
within a couple weeks.

00:12:57.250 --> 00:12:59.050 align:middle line:84%
And we had been trying
for a few months.

00:12:59.050 --> 00:13:00.226 align:middle line:90%
So....

00:13:00.226 --> 00:13:02.120 align:middle line:84%
Just think, this was
your eighth birthday

00:13:02.120 --> 00:13:04.690 align:middle line:84%
party because we had a costume
party and you were a samurai.

00:13:04.690 --> 00:13:07.015 align:middle line:84%
It was a major--
everybody dressed up.

00:13:07.015 --> 00:13:08.980 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I remember that outfit.

00:13:08.980 --> 00:13:10.980 align:middle line:90%
I loved that outfit.

00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:12.020 align:middle line:90%
DIANA MUKPO: It was so great.

00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:16.214 align:middle line:90%


00:13:16.214 --> 00:13:21.094 align:middle line:90%
[HORSE WHINNIES]

00:13:21.094 --> 00:13:24.520 align:middle line:90%


00:13:24.520 --> 00:13:27.090 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: My mother
was born in London in 1953

00:13:27.090 --> 00:13:30.420 align:middle line:84%
to an upper class British
family, her father a barrister

00:13:30.420 --> 00:13:33.930 align:middle line:90%
and her mother an opera singer.

00:13:33.930 --> 00:13:38.170 align:middle line:84%
My father was born in a
tent on the plains of Tibet.

00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.410 align:middle line:84%
When he was 18 months
old, a group of monks

00:13:40.410 --> 00:13:41.990 align:middle line:84%
would show up at the
tent door to declare

00:13:41.990 --> 00:13:45.300 align:middle line:84%
him the reincarnation
of their teacher.

00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:46.720 align:middle line:84%
He would be raised
in a monastery

00:13:46.720 --> 00:13:49.810 align:middle line:84%
until he was 19, when he
fled Tibet on the heels

00:13:49.810 --> 00:13:52.150 align:middle line:90%
of the Chinese invasion.

00:13:52.150 --> 00:13:55.555 align:middle line:84%
A brilliant mind, four years
after arriving in India,

00:13:55.555 --> 00:13:58.155 align:middle line:84%
he would end up in England
attending Oxford University

00:13:58.155 --> 00:14:00.480 align:middle line:90%
on a Spalding scholarship.

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:04.154 align:middle line:84%
It was there that he
and my mother met.

00:14:04.154 --> 00:14:05.420 align:middle line:84%
DIANA MUKPO: I heard
that he was going

00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:09.080 align:middle line:84%
to be giving a talk
at a rally for Tibetan

00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:10.840 align:middle line:90%
liberation in London.

00:14:10.840 --> 00:14:12.780 align:middle line:84%
And that was the first
time I set eyes on him.

00:14:12.780 --> 00:14:15.040 align:middle line:84%
And I felt an immediate and
instant connection with him

00:14:15.040 --> 00:14:18.200 align:middle line:84%
as soon as he walked
onto the stage.

00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:20.050 align:middle line:84%
So after that, I
resolved to meet him.

00:14:20.050 --> 00:14:24.110 align:middle line:90%


00:14:24.110 --> 00:14:26.790 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't expect to
have the kind of reaction

00:14:26.790 --> 00:14:28.420 align:middle line:84%
that I had when I
just set eyes on him.

00:14:28.420 --> 00:14:31.210 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I'd known him
for lifetimes the first time

00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:32.290 align:middle line:90%
I saw him.

00:14:32.290 --> 00:14:37.210 align:middle line:84%
It was immediate, instantaneous,
incredible connection.

00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:38.560 align:middle line:90%
And the rest is history.

00:14:38.560 --> 00:14:43.850 align:middle line:90%


00:14:43.850 --> 00:14:48.090 align:middle line:84%
There were a lot of hippy
types, but generally, really

00:14:48.090 --> 00:14:49.400 align:middle line:90%
sort of the intelligentsia.

00:14:49.400 --> 00:14:51.660 align:middle line:10%
Very, very smart people
were attracted to him.

00:14:51.660 --> 00:14:55.330 align:middle line:10%
And he was brilliant and wasn't
threatened by that at all.

00:14:55.330 --> 00:14:58.090 align:middle line:10%
So people who were
very, very smart,

00:14:58.090 --> 00:15:02.220 align:middle line:10%
most of them college educated,
who actually were really

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:04.490 align:middle line:10%
seeking something
that would make more

00:15:04.490 --> 00:15:06.555 align:middle line:10%
sense to them than what
they had been raised with.

00:15:06.555 --> 00:15:11.180 align:middle line:90%


00:15:11.180 --> 00:15:12.480 align:middle line:90%
We spent some time together.

00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:15.160 align:middle line:84%
And he said to me, sometime,
I'd love to marry you.

00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:18.080 align:middle line:84%
And I said to him, well,
I'd like to marry you, too.

00:15:18.080 --> 00:15:21.360 align:middle line:84%
And then we discovered
that January 1, 1970,

00:15:21.360 --> 00:15:23.570 align:middle line:84%
there had been a law
passed in Scotland

00:15:23.570 --> 00:15:26.570 align:middle line:84%
that you could get married at 16
without your parents' consent.

00:15:26.570 --> 00:15:31.470 align:middle line:10%
So on January the 3rd, 1970, I
eloped with him to Edinburgh,

00:15:31.470 --> 00:15:34.870 align:middle line:10%
where we got married,
which was less than three

00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:38.500 align:middle line:10%
months after my 16th birthday.

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:41.770 align:middle line:10%
My mother found out from
the newspaper reporters that

00:15:41.770 --> 00:15:45.100 align:middle line:10%
knocked on her door in
London and said to her,

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:47.700 align:middle line:10%
we'd like to find out
about your daughter

00:15:47.700 --> 00:15:48.990 align:middle line:10%
who married the Tibetan monk.

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:50.290 align:middle line:90%
And she said, oh, my God.

00:15:50.290 --> 00:15:51.420 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my God.

00:15:51.420 --> 00:15:52.780 align:middle line:90%
Tessa got married.

00:15:52.780 --> 00:15:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And Tessa was my older sister
who at that time was 19.

00:15:55.750 --> 00:15:58.080 align:middle line:84%
And they said, no,
no, it was Diana.

00:15:58.080 --> 00:15:58.805 align:middle line:90%
And she fainted.

00:15:58.805 --> 00:16:01.950 align:middle line:90%


00:16:01.950 --> 00:16:04.730 align:middle line:84%
All the kids were really
excited that Diana had done

00:16:04.730 --> 00:16:07.268 align:middle line:90%
a very cool thing. [LAUGHS]

00:16:07.268 --> 00:16:12.470 align:middle line:90%


00:16:12.470 --> 00:16:13.850 align:middle line:90%
I mean, he loved you very much.

00:16:13.850 --> 00:16:16.450 align:middle line:90%
He believed in you 100%.

00:16:16.450 --> 00:16:19.810 align:middle line:84%
He was really concerned
about your education

00:16:19.810 --> 00:16:23.420 align:middle line:84%
and felt very strongly that you
could grow up and become a very

00:16:23.420 --> 00:16:25.990 align:middle line:84%
powerful Buddhist teacher
and wanted to create the best

00:16:25.990 --> 00:16:30.110 align:middle line:84%
environment for you to grow
up and be educated to be

00:16:30.110 --> 00:16:33.017 align:middle line:90%
able to go in that direction.

00:16:33.017 --> 00:16:34.150 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: If
my father believed

00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:38.050 align:middle line:84%
I could become a Buddhist
teacher yet didn't send me off

00:16:38.050 --> 00:16:41.710 align:middle line:84%
to a Buddhist monastery,
then what exactly did he

00:16:41.710 --> 00:16:42.844 align:middle line:90%
have in mind?

00:16:42.844 --> 00:16:47.290 align:middle line:90%
[WIND BLOWING]

00:16:47.290 --> 00:16:51.242 align:middle line:90%
[BRASS BAND PLAYING]

00:16:51.242 --> 00:17:00.640 align:middle line:90%


00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:05.560 align:middle line:84%
Being a tulku born in the West
is an interesting predicament.

00:17:05.560 --> 00:17:06.930 align:middle line:84%
There is no
predetermined course.

00:17:06.930 --> 00:17:09.628 align:middle line:84%
So it's impossible to tell
whether you're on track or not.

00:17:09.628 --> 00:17:22.156 align:middle line:90%


00:17:22.156 --> 00:17:24.400 align:middle line:84%
With that in mind, I
head to New York City

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:26.910 align:middle line:84%
to meet another
Western tulku, Ashoka,

00:17:26.910 --> 00:17:29.780 align:middle line:84%
and find out how he has dealt
with his unusual circumstance.

00:17:29.780 --> 00:17:35.192 align:middle line:90%
[BRASS BAND PLAYING]

00:17:35.192 --> 00:17:49.460 align:middle line:90%


00:17:49.460 --> 00:17:53.700 align:middle line:84%
Ashoka and I have something
else in common, our mother.

00:17:53.700 --> 00:17:55.790 align:middle line:90%
Ashoka is my younger brother.

00:17:55.790 --> 00:17:58.370 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTING]

00:17:58.370 --> 00:18:00.050 align:middle line:90%


00:18:00.050 --> 00:18:02.690 align:middle line:84%
In Tibet, it was not unusual
for more than one tulku

00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:04.090 align:middle line:90%
to be born into the same family.

00:18:04.090 --> 00:18:15.390 align:middle line:90%


00:18:15.390 --> 00:18:18.650 align:middle line:84%
This is actually a painting
of the previous incarnation

00:18:18.650 --> 00:18:20.680 align:middle line:90%
of Khamyon Rinpoche.

00:18:20.680 --> 00:18:22.590 align:middle line:84%
So you know, I
obviously say a lot

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:26.920 align:middle line:84%
that I have a very hard
time with being a tulku,

00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:30.145 align:middle line:84%
yet I still display this thangka
of my previous incarnations.

00:18:30.145 --> 00:18:31.690 align:middle line:90%
So I don't know what that says.

00:18:31.690 --> 00:18:33.740 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:18:33.740 --> 00:18:35.885 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Why do you
think they gave it to you?

00:18:35.885 --> 00:18:37.450 align:middle line:84%
I think that they
gave it to me,

00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:40.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure, because they believe
that I am the incarnation

00:18:40.150 --> 00:18:41.260 align:middle line:90%
of their previous teacher.

00:18:41.260 --> 00:18:44.180 align:middle line:84%
And that's what's so
hard about it, you know?

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:47.340 align:middle line:84%
It wouldn't matter if I believed
that I was the incarnation

00:18:47.340 --> 00:18:48.830 align:middle line:84%
of Khamyon Rinpoche
if I was teaching

00:18:48.830 --> 00:18:50.350 align:middle line:84%
and if I'd gone through
all that training.

00:18:50.350 --> 00:18:52.050 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have to
worry so much about that

00:18:52.050 --> 00:18:53.606 align:middle line:84%
because I'd actually
be fulfilling that role

00:18:53.606 --> 00:18:54.305 align:middle line:90%
that they need.

00:18:54.305 --> 00:18:57.100 align:middle line:90%


00:18:57.100 --> 00:18:58.270 align:middle line:84%
When I was in Tibet,
I mean, it was

00:18:58.270 --> 00:18:59.670 align:middle line:90%
a really intense experience.

00:18:59.670 --> 00:19:04.030 align:middle line:84%
I was enthroned, which is
essentially their way of kind

00:19:04.030 --> 00:19:08.520 align:middle line:84%
of sanctifying the recognition
of the next incarnation

00:19:08.520 --> 00:19:09.610 align:middle line:90%
of a Rinpoche.

00:19:09.610 --> 00:19:12.180 align:middle line:84%
So another lama will
perform a ceremony

00:19:12.180 --> 00:19:15.270 align:middle line:84%
where they sort of impart the
blessings and the artifacts

00:19:15.270 --> 00:19:16.870 align:middle line:90%
of the previous incarnation.

00:19:16.870 --> 00:19:20.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's sort of the
official stamp of approval

00:19:20.020 --> 00:19:24.802 align:middle line:84%
that you now hold that role
and you hold that seat.

00:19:24.802 --> 00:19:29.090 align:middle line:84%
At one point, a man
who was the younger

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:32.190 align:middle line:84%
brother of the previous
Khamyon Rinpoche came up to me.

00:19:32.190 --> 00:19:33.460 align:middle line:90%
And he was a very old man.

00:19:33.460 --> 00:19:36.590 align:middle line:84%
And he was just tears
streaming down his face.

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:38.155 align:middle line:84%
And you kind of
feel a little bit

00:19:38.155 --> 00:19:39.830 align:middle line:90%
like a deer in the headlights.

00:19:39.830 --> 00:19:41.160 align:middle line:90%
What do you offer to somebody?

00:19:41.160 --> 00:19:44.560 align:middle line:84%
So I try to just be
there as much as I can.

00:19:44.560 --> 00:19:47.320 align:middle line:90%


00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:48.140 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:51.014 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what the fuck.

00:19:51.014 --> 00:19:52.008 align:middle line:90%
Oh, God.

00:19:52.008 --> 00:20:05.924 align:middle line:90%


00:20:05.924 --> 00:20:07.912 align:middle line:90%
And good morning.

00:20:07.912 --> 00:20:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Have a great day, ma'am.
Morning!

00:20:09.900 --> 00:20:14.731 align:middle line:90%


00:20:14.731 --> 00:20:15.864 align:middle line:84%
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Please stand away

00:20:15.864 --> 00:20:17.852 align:middle line:90%
from the bright yellow strip.

00:20:17.852 --> 00:20:20.860 align:middle line:90%
[MAN SINGING]

00:20:20.860 --> 00:20:23.100 align:middle line:84%
ASHOKA MUKPO: I don't
think that my role

00:20:23.100 --> 00:20:24.920 align:middle line:84%
is to be a teacher, to
be wearing the robes

00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:26.640 align:middle line:90%
and be up on a throne.

00:20:26.640 --> 00:20:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And if that makes
me a failed tulku,

00:20:28.530 --> 00:20:30.010 align:middle line:90%
then maybe that's just my karma.

00:20:30.010 --> 00:20:36.570 align:middle line:90%


00:20:36.570 --> 00:20:38.440 align:middle line:84%
But I still think I can
be of some kind of benefit

00:20:38.440 --> 00:20:39.930 align:middle line:90%
to somebody.

00:20:39.930 --> 00:20:42.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's, I think, what
being a Buddhist is about.

00:20:42.100 --> 00:20:52.760 align:middle line:90%


00:20:52.760 --> 00:20:56.080 align:middle line:84%
I work at Human
Rights Watch, which

00:20:56.080 --> 00:21:01.360 align:middle line:84%
is a nonprofit
organization that monitors

00:21:01.360 --> 00:21:03.220 align:middle line:84%
human rights conditions
in different countries

00:21:03.220 --> 00:21:04.180 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:06.350 align:middle line:84%
I work for the program
that does prison conditions

00:21:06.350 --> 00:21:07.780 align:middle line:90%
inside of the United States.

00:21:07.780 --> 00:21:12.100 align:middle line:84%
So we really look at the
situation for people who

00:21:12.100 --> 00:21:14.950 align:middle line:84%
are incarcerated
in America and we

00:21:14.950 --> 00:21:16.860 align:middle line:84%
try to investigate
situations where

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:19.750 align:middle line:84%
we feel like the standard
of care for those prisoners

00:21:19.750 --> 00:21:20.990 align:middle line:90%
isn't being met.

00:21:20.990 --> 00:21:23.280 align:middle line:84%
And we try to get certain
policies changed that we think

00:21:23.280 --> 00:21:26.145 align:middle line:84%
are not beneficial
for the rehabilitation

00:21:26.145 --> 00:21:27.594 align:middle line:90%
of prisoners who are in jail.

00:21:27.594 --> 00:21:31.550 align:middle line:90%


00:21:31.550 --> 00:21:33.036 align:middle line:84%
Hi, is this Kevin?
Hi, Kevin.

00:21:33.036 --> 00:21:33.735 align:middle line:90%
How are you doing?

00:21:33.735 --> 00:21:35.280 align:middle line:84%
This is Ashoka from
Human Rights Watch.

00:21:35.280 --> 00:21:36.820 align:middle line:84%
I'm just following
up on a phone call

00:21:36.820 --> 00:21:38.600 align:middle line:84%
that you gave to
us the other day.

00:21:38.600 --> 00:21:41.754 align:middle line:84%
I think if the police aren't
handling this appropriately,

00:21:41.754 --> 00:21:43.520 align:middle line:84%
it might be worthwhile for
you to think about getting

00:21:43.520 --> 00:21:44.386 align:middle line:90%
some legal representation.

00:21:44.386 --> 00:21:51.277 align:middle line:90%


00:21:51.277 --> 00:21:51.976 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:21:51.976 --> 00:21:54.800 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think there's
a lot of people like you

00:21:54.800 --> 00:21:57.020 align:middle line:84%
who were not arrested
for violent crimes

00:21:57.020 --> 00:22:00.870 align:middle line:84%
and who weren't arrested
for the types of crimes

00:22:00.870 --> 00:22:05.210 align:middle line:84%
that typically people think are
the crimes that people who are

00:22:05.210 --> 00:22:06.380 align:middle line:90%
on the registry have committed.

00:22:06.380 --> 00:22:08.246 align:middle line:84%
But then, they're subject to
the same kind of harassment

00:22:08.246 --> 00:22:11.250 align:middle line:84%
and lack of employment and
those kinds of problems

00:22:11.250 --> 00:22:14.791 align:middle line:84%
that it sounds like
you're running across.

00:22:14.791 --> 00:22:15.490 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:22:15.490 --> 00:22:20.180 align:middle line:90%


00:22:20.180 --> 00:22:24.920 align:middle line:84%
I've always really felt
like helping people

00:22:24.920 --> 00:22:29.040 align:middle line:84%
from the perspective
of being an educated

00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:31.615 align:middle line:84%
Westerner who came from, like,
a pretty well-off family.

00:22:31.615 --> 00:22:34.490 align:middle line:90%


00:22:34.490 --> 00:22:37.340 align:middle line:10%
It's important to
give something back.

00:22:37.340 --> 00:22:39.540 align:middle line:10%
I think I've at this
point pretty much decided

00:22:39.540 --> 00:22:40.910 align:middle line:10%
that, whatever I
do with my life,

00:22:40.910 --> 00:22:43.330 align:middle line:10%
I want to have it be
about at least trying

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:45.220 align:middle line:10%
to make the world a little
bit of a better place

00:22:45.220 --> 00:22:47.239 align:middle line:10%
because there's a lot
of problems out there.

00:22:47.239 --> 00:22:52.229 align:middle line:90%
[BRASS BAND PLAYS]

00:22:52.229 --> 00:23:37.847 align:middle line:90%


00:23:37.847 --> 00:23:38.980 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: What
about the tulkus

00:23:38.980 --> 00:23:41.880 align:middle line:84%
who have actually lived up to
the tremendous expectations

00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:42.620 align:middle line:90%
placed on them?

00:23:42.620 --> 00:23:45.820 align:middle line:90%


00:23:45.820 --> 00:23:48.460 align:middle line:84%
In my eyes, the living
embodiment of this

00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:51.810 align:middle line:84%
is my teacher, Dzongsar Khyentse
Rinpoche, a renowned Buddhist

00:23:51.810 --> 00:23:54.270 align:middle line:90%
master and filmmaker.

00:23:54.270 --> 00:23:57.830 align:middle line:84%
So in hopes of tracking
him down, I get on a plane

00:23:57.830 --> 00:23:59.120 align:middle line:90%
and travel to northern India.

00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:01.105 align:middle line:90%


00:24:01.105 --> 00:24:06.055 align:middle line:90%
[EXOTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:06.055 --> 00:24:25.360 align:middle line:90%


00:24:25.360 --> 00:24:29.440 align:middle line:84%
India is the
birthplace of Buddhism.

00:24:29.440 --> 00:24:33.070 align:middle line:84%
2,500 years ago, Siddharta
Gautama came into this world

00:24:33.070 --> 00:24:35.570 align:middle line:84%
and eventually became one of
the most influential figures

00:24:35.570 --> 00:24:37.284 align:middle line:90%
in history.

00:24:37.284 --> 00:24:42.751 align:middle line:90%
[INDIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:42.751 --> 00:25:17.550 align:middle line:90%


00:25:17.550 --> 00:25:20.640 align:middle line:84%
In 1959, during the
Chinese invasion,

00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:22.650 align:middle line:84%
many Tibetans fled
to India, where

00:25:22.650 --> 00:25:24.600 align:middle line:84%
the Indian government
helped them establish

00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:26.790 align:middle line:90%
Tibetan refugee settlements.

00:25:26.790 --> 00:25:29.190 align:middle line:84%
One of these settlements,
perched in the Himalayan

00:25:29.190 --> 00:25:30.750 align:middle line:90%
foothills, was Bir.

00:25:30.750 --> 00:25:36.200 align:middle line:90%


00:25:36.200 --> 00:25:38.645 align:middle line:10%
This was my father's
first stop when he escaped

00:25:38.645 --> 00:25:40.650 align:middle line:10%
to India almost 50 years ago.

00:25:40.650 --> 00:25:44.370 align:middle line:90%


00:25:44.370 --> 00:25:48.082 align:middle line:84%
Today, Bir has grown into a
thriving Tibetan community.

00:25:48.082 --> 00:25:51.058 align:middle line:90%


00:25:51.058 --> 00:25:53.538 align:middle line:90%
[DOG BARKS]

00:25:53.538 --> 00:26:12.910 align:middle line:90%


00:26:12.910 --> 00:26:17.050 align:middle line:84%
Without looking back, we
can never move forward.

00:26:17.050 --> 00:26:21.372 align:middle line:84%
But without moving forward, we
are simply stuck in the past.

00:26:21.372 --> 00:26:27.760 align:middle line:90%
[MONKS CHANTING]

00:26:27.760 --> 00:26:30.440 align:middle line:84%
When I was a child, the
idea of being a tulku

00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:32.970 align:middle line:90%
seemed completely normal.

00:26:32.970 --> 00:26:35.430 align:middle line:84%
By the time I hit my teens, I
started to find the whole thing

00:26:35.430 --> 00:26:38.310 align:middle line:84%
crazy and wondered if someone
was playing some kind of joke

00:26:38.310 --> 00:26:39.219 align:middle line:90%
on me.

00:26:39.219 --> 00:26:44.009 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:26:44.009 --> 00:26:46.890 align:middle line:90%


00:26:46.890 --> 00:26:49.260 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't unusual to have
one of my father's students

00:26:49.260 --> 00:26:52.730 align:middle line:84%
ask me for advice when I
was only 11 or 12 years old.

00:26:52.730 --> 00:26:58.230 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:26:58.230 --> 00:27:07.230 align:middle line:90%


00:27:07.230 --> 00:27:13.730 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:27:13.730 --> 00:27:15.960 align:middle line:84%
I've always felt I have
some kind of obligation

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:17.510 align:middle line:90%
that people expected from me.

00:27:17.510 --> 00:27:21.660 align:middle line:84%
But I could never figure
out exactly what it was.

00:27:21.660 --> 00:27:23.770 align:middle line:84%
And how could I fill
these obligations

00:27:23.770 --> 00:27:25.617 align:middle line:90%
if I'm just an ordinary person?

00:27:25.617 --> 00:27:30.587 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:27:30.587 --> 00:27:52.000 align:middle line:90%


00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:54.260 align:middle line:84%
I first met Dzongsar
Khyentse Rinpoche,

00:27:54.260 --> 00:27:56.540 align:middle line:84%
my teacher, when I
was 16 years old,

00:27:56.540 --> 00:27:58.590 align:middle line:84%
and was immediately
drawn to him.

00:27:58.590 --> 00:28:01.240 align:middle line:84%
A few years later, instead
of going to college,

00:28:01.240 --> 00:28:03.098 align:middle line:84%
I went to India
to study with him.

00:28:03.098 --> 00:28:07.490 align:middle line:90%
[RAGTIME MUSIC]

00:28:07.490 --> 00:28:08.466 align:middle line:90%


00:28:08.466 --> 00:28:11.882 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTING, LAUGHING]

00:28:11.882 --> 00:28:17.740 align:middle line:90%


00:28:17.740 --> 00:28:19.800 align:middle line:84%
I've always valued his
guidance and insight.

00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And I'm hoping to spend
some time with him.

00:28:22.780 --> 00:28:25.342 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, I'm
not the only one.

00:28:25.342 --> 00:28:29.278 align:middle line:90%
[RAGTIME MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:28:29.278 --> 00:28:33.706 align:middle line:90%


00:28:33.706 --> 00:28:38.626 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTING]

00:28:38.626 --> 00:29:45.131 align:middle line:90%


00:29:45.131 --> 00:29:46.664 align:middle line:84%
DZONGSAR KHYENTSE RINPOCHE:
Really, seriously.

00:29:46.664 --> 00:29:55.150 align:middle line:90%


00:29:55.150 --> 00:29:57.310 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Raised as a
tulku in the traditional way,

00:29:57.310 --> 00:30:00.090 align:middle line:84%
he underwent an
extensive education.

00:30:00.090 --> 00:30:03.210 align:middle line:84%
He's also a filmmaker whose
debut film was well received

00:30:03.210 --> 00:30:04.270 align:middle line:90%
at the Cannes Film Festival.

00:30:04.270 --> 00:30:06.870 align:middle line:90%


00:30:06.870 --> 00:30:08.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm very traditional.

00:30:08.550 --> 00:30:10.470 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:30:10.470 --> 00:30:12.996 align:middle line:84%
There's so many new
tulkus you must have met.

00:30:12.996 --> 00:30:13.695 align:middle line:90%
Oh, God.

00:30:13.695 --> 00:30:16.850 align:middle line:90%


00:30:16.850 --> 00:30:19.980 align:middle line:84%
And actually, many of them,
they behave, you know.

00:30:19.980 --> 00:30:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And even they behave,
thousand of them

00:30:24.530 --> 00:30:29.490 align:middle line:84%
and this man who
misbehave, I prefer him.

00:30:29.490 --> 00:30:33.690 align:middle line:84%
That's another thing
I can tell you.

00:30:33.690 --> 00:30:35.702 align:middle line:90%
We're still waiting.

00:30:35.702 --> 00:30:41.130 align:middle line:84%
We are still waiting for him
to do what he's supposed to do.

00:30:41.130 --> 00:30:43.730 align:middle line:84%
That's what I have to say.
What do you think?

00:30:43.730 --> 00:30:47.514 align:middle line:90%


00:30:47.514 --> 00:30:48.460 align:middle line:90%
Hmm?

00:30:48.460 --> 00:30:52.010 align:middle line:84%
Tibetan lamas, especially high
lamas like Karmapa in your case

00:30:52.010 --> 00:30:55.050 align:middle line:84%
or Dilgo Khyentse
Rinpoche, beginning

00:30:55.050 --> 00:31:01.510 align:middle line:84%
to find tulkus in the West is
very encouraging because this

00:31:01.510 --> 00:31:06.210 align:middle line:84%
actually shows there
is no nepotism,

00:31:06.210 --> 00:31:09.080 align:middle line:84%
like that tulkus will
always-- that Westerners,

00:31:09.080 --> 00:31:10.795 align:middle line:90%
you're all doom.

00:31:10.795 --> 00:31:13.020 align:middle line:84%
You'll never be a
Buddhist incarnation.

00:31:13.020 --> 00:31:14.890 align:middle line:90%
You understand what I'm saying.

00:31:14.890 --> 00:31:17.910 align:middle line:90%
And this is a great thing.

00:31:17.910 --> 00:31:21.080 align:middle line:90%
I think there should be more.

00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:24.870 align:middle line:90%
OK, if it was done properly.

00:31:24.870 --> 00:31:30.060 align:middle line:90%


00:31:30.060 --> 00:31:33.970 align:middle line:90%
Because from two points.

00:31:33.970 --> 00:31:36.730 align:middle line:84%
From the reincarnation's
point of view,

00:31:36.730 --> 00:31:39.434 align:middle line:84%
reincarnation does not--
like the Tibetans don't

00:31:39.434 --> 00:31:40.400 align:middle line:90%
end up becoming only Tibetan.

00:31:40.400 --> 00:31:43.050 align:middle line:90%


00:31:43.050 --> 00:31:47.410 align:middle line:84%
The transmigration
happens everywhere.

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:49.920 align:middle line:84%
In fact, some of the high
lamas, for the benefit

00:31:49.920 --> 00:31:52.260 align:middle line:84%
of sentient beings,
they must reincarnate

00:31:52.260 --> 00:31:55.950 align:middle line:90%
as a bird or a lizard.

00:31:55.950 --> 00:31:58.230 align:middle line:84%
But we human beings don't
want to really think

00:31:58.230 --> 00:32:02.380 align:middle line:84%
in terms of enthroning a
lizard as the seat holder

00:32:02.380 --> 00:32:05.730 align:middle line:90%
of your big monastery, do you?

00:32:05.730 --> 00:32:08.110 align:middle line:90%
Similarly, manifestation also.

00:32:08.110 --> 00:32:11.210 align:middle line:90%
Wherever it benefits.

00:32:11.210 --> 00:32:12.440 align:middle line:90%
Wherever it benefits.

00:32:12.440 --> 00:32:16.020 align:middle line:90%


00:32:16.020 --> 00:32:20.012 align:middle line:84%
Wherever the reincarnation
benefits, even as a lizard.

00:32:20.012 --> 00:32:27.392 align:middle line:90%
[BIRDS CALLING]

00:32:27.392 --> 00:32:35.280 align:middle line:90%


00:32:35.280 --> 00:32:38.190 align:middle line:84%
[MUSIC PLAYING, DON BROWNRIGG,
 "IN IT"]

00:32:38.190 --> 00:33:10.677 align:middle line:90%


00:33:10.677 --> 00:33:11.910 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: I found
out that there's

00:33:11.910 --> 00:33:15.520 align:middle line:84%
this young tulku named
Wyatt, who's 23 or somewhere

00:33:15.520 --> 00:33:17.570 align:middle line:90%
in that range.

00:33:17.570 --> 00:33:21.370 align:middle line:84%
And my teacher, Dzongsar
Khyentse Rinpoche, I guess,

00:33:21.370 --> 00:33:26.360 align:middle line:84%
told him to study Tibetan
or something like that.

00:33:26.360 --> 00:33:27.860 align:middle line:90%
So yeah, I want to give a call.

00:33:27.860 --> 00:33:29.890 align:middle line:90%
I have his cell phone number.

00:33:29.890 --> 00:33:34.070 align:middle line:84%
And give him a call and see
if we could get together.

00:33:34.070 --> 00:33:38.180 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not sure if I'm going
to get in touch with him.

00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:40.452 align:middle line:90%
But why not give it a shot?

00:33:40.452 --> 00:33:42.356 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:33:42.356 --> 00:33:47.592 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:33:47.592 --> 00:33:50.110 align:middle line:90%
Maybe he's class, though.

00:33:50.110 --> 00:33:53.120 align:middle line:90%
Hopefully, he's in class.

00:33:53.120 --> 00:33:55.020 align:middle line:90%
["IN IT" CONTINUES]

00:33:55.020 --> 00:34:16.244 align:middle line:90%


00:34:16.244 --> 00:34:19.634 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:34:19.634 --> 00:34:23.854 align:middle line:90%


00:34:23.854 --> 00:34:25.215 align:middle line:84%
--[TEACHER SPEAKING TIBETAN]
Good.

00:34:25.215 --> 00:34:45.633 align:middle line:90%


00:34:45.633 --> 00:34:48.621 align:middle line:90%
[HORN HONKS]

00:34:48.621 --> 00:34:56.610 align:middle line:90%


00:34:56.610 --> 00:34:57.850 align:middle line:90%
GESAR MUKPO: Oh, hey, Wyatt!

00:34:57.850 --> 00:34:59.135 align:middle line:90%
By the way, Gesar.

00:34:59.135 --> 00:34:59.920 align:middle line:90%
Nice to meet you.

00:34:59.920 --> 00:35:00.967 align:middle line:90%
Where are you from?

00:35:00.967 --> 00:35:02.790 align:middle line:90%
San Francisco.

00:35:02.790 --> 00:35:04.150 align:middle line:90%
I live in Canada now.

00:35:04.150 --> 00:35:06.240 align:middle line:90%
So thanks for coming, man.

00:35:06.240 --> 00:35:07.510 align:middle line:90%
Let me buy you dinner?

00:35:07.510 --> 00:35:08.245 align:middle line:90%
OK, yeah.

00:35:08.245 --> 00:35:11.167 align:middle line:90%


00:35:11.167 --> 00:35:12.300 align:middle line:84%
WYATT ARNOLD: Like,
I was supposed

00:35:12.300 --> 00:35:14.100 align:middle line:90%
to go to India when I was five.

00:35:14.100 --> 00:35:16.400 align:middle line:84%
My father wanted to
raise me in the West.

00:35:16.400 --> 00:35:21.850 align:middle line:84%
And my mother didn't want to let
me go halfway around the world.

00:35:21.850 --> 00:35:25.580 align:middle line:84%
I ended up not going to
India until just a year ago.

00:35:25.580 --> 00:35:28.640 align:middle line:90%


00:35:28.640 --> 00:35:35.610 align:middle line:84%
I was recognized and enthroned
when I was five years

00:35:35.610 --> 00:35:40.060 align:middle line:90%
old by Chagdud Tulku Rinpoche.

00:35:40.060 --> 00:35:41.360 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't scared.

00:35:41.360 --> 00:35:44.210 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't nervous.

00:35:44.210 --> 00:35:46.210 align:middle line:90%
And it was very relaxed.

00:35:46.210 --> 00:35:47.380 align:middle line:90%
But it was very intense.

00:35:47.380 --> 00:35:51.910 align:middle line:90%


00:35:51.910 --> 00:35:54.660 align:middle line:84%
I think when you're a kid,
it's easier for people

00:35:54.660 --> 00:35:57.396 align:middle line:84%
to accept because
you're so innocent.

00:35:57.396 --> 00:35:59.890 align:middle line:90%
You're so fresh.

00:35:59.890 --> 00:36:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And you're not worried
about their expectations.

00:36:03.850 --> 00:36:07.030 align:middle line:84%
So it was easy for
them to believe

00:36:07.030 --> 00:36:08.760 align:middle line:90%
because it's just a boy.

00:36:08.760 --> 00:36:16.500 align:middle line:90%


00:36:16.500 --> 00:36:21.665 align:middle line:84%
In Catholic prep school, I was
known as the Little Dalai Lama.

00:36:21.665 --> 00:36:27.000 align:middle line:90%


00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:31.210 align:middle line:84%
When I was a kid,
I would say things.

00:36:31.210 --> 00:36:34.860 align:middle line:10%
You know, I remember you and me
hanging out in this courtyard

00:36:34.860 --> 00:36:38.810 align:middle line:10%
in such-and-such a gompa,
in such-and-such a time

00:36:38.810 --> 00:36:40.725 align:middle line:10%
and such-and-such
a place in Tibet.

00:36:40.725 --> 00:36:43.550 align:middle line:90%


00:36:43.550 --> 00:36:46.300 align:middle line:84%
For Chagdud Tulku,
being around him

00:36:46.300 --> 00:36:48.710 align:middle line:84%
was like being
with a grandfather.

00:36:48.710 --> 00:36:52.960 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he sort of
was always looking

00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:55.220 align:middle line:90%
after me, disciplining me.

00:36:55.220 --> 00:36:57.500 align:middle line:84%
He taught me
Tibetan for a while.

00:36:57.500 --> 00:37:00.400 align:middle line:84%
He taught me how to read
Tibetan when I was little.

00:37:00.400 --> 00:37:03.850 align:middle line:84%
He had me on the throne
always next to him.

00:37:03.850 --> 00:37:08.080 align:middle line:84%
And I'd have to read
my text during puja.

00:37:08.080 --> 00:37:09.950 align:middle line:90%
All sorts of practices.

00:37:09.950 --> 00:37:12.000 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, and of course,
being around him

00:37:12.000 --> 00:37:15.610 align:middle line:84%
was so-- I loved
being around him.

00:37:15.610 --> 00:37:16.830 align:middle line:90%
I mean, how could I not?

00:37:16.830 --> 00:37:18.770 align:middle line:90%
He was just so kind.

00:37:18.770 --> 00:37:21.760 align:middle line:90%
He would give everything to me.

00:37:21.760 --> 00:37:28.410 align:middle line:84%
He'd just always look at me
with those eyes of-- just

00:37:28.410 --> 00:37:31.690 align:middle line:90%
like-- how do you say?

00:37:31.690 --> 00:37:33.790 align:middle line:84%
You know, those
eyes that you want

00:37:33.790 --> 00:37:42.950 align:middle line:84%
everybody to look at you with,
those eyes of just such care,

00:37:42.950 --> 00:37:44.830 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:37:44.830 --> 00:37:47.517 align:middle line:84%
I don't know so many
good words for it.

00:37:47.517 --> 00:37:50.140 align:middle line:90%


00:37:50.140 --> 00:37:53.100 align:middle line:84%
That whole phase was
until I was eight.

00:37:53.100 --> 00:37:57.925 align:middle line:84%
After that, being around
him, we didn't talk so much.

00:37:57.925 --> 00:38:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And I went to him one day,
I think maybe in 2000,

00:38:01.520 --> 00:38:03.527 align:middle line:84%
right before I was
entering high school.

00:38:03.527 --> 00:38:05.790 align:middle line:84%
And I was like,
what should I do.

00:38:05.790 --> 00:38:08.880 align:middle line:84%
And Rinpoche was like,
listen to your father.

00:38:08.880 --> 00:38:16.446 align:middle line:84%
So after that, he sort of--
I mean, eased off a lot.

00:38:16.446 --> 00:38:21.495 align:middle line:90%
And I changed after that.

00:38:21.495 --> 00:38:23.580 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how to explain it.

00:38:23.580 --> 00:38:28.040 align:middle line:84%
But some days I felt like, oh,
maybe he doesn't care anymore.

00:38:28.040 --> 00:38:34.470 align:middle line:84%
But then there was-- I still
saw those eyes, of course.

00:38:34.470 --> 00:38:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And I had taken an
interest in lama dancing.

00:38:39.270 --> 00:38:40.510 align:middle line:90%
I was so into it.

00:38:40.510 --> 00:38:42.360 align:middle line:84%
Like, I was just
into this thing.

00:38:42.360 --> 00:38:48.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you put on this huge
costume that weighs maybe 30

00:38:48.780 --> 00:38:54.070 align:middle line:84%
pounds, and this mask
that digs into your head,

00:38:54.070 --> 00:38:56.820 align:middle line:84%
like you got to put
all these pads in it.

00:38:56.820 --> 00:38:59.245 align:middle line:90%
And it's like, these huge teeth.

00:38:59.245 --> 00:39:01.400 align:middle line:84%
And you wear a
costume like that.

00:39:01.400 --> 00:39:07.000 align:middle line:84%
And you just spin around
and jump up in the air.

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:09.880 align:middle line:90%
And it's really exciting.

00:39:09.880 --> 00:39:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And I enjoyed it so much
that when I sat back down

00:39:15.840 --> 00:39:18.680 align:middle line:84%
and looked up to him, and
he was like-- I had never

00:39:18.680 --> 00:39:21.880 align:middle line:90%
seen him so content with me.

00:39:21.880 --> 00:39:24.340 align:middle line:84%
I was always worried
about his approval.

00:39:24.340 --> 00:39:27.390 align:middle line:90%
And after that, it just--

00:39:27.390 --> 00:39:32.260 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it was the whole-- I think
it was just the whole ceremony.

00:39:32.260 --> 00:39:38.420 align:middle line:84%
And he looked so just
really happy, happy

00:39:38.420 --> 00:39:41.060 align:middle line:90%
about everything that had gone.

00:39:41.060 --> 00:39:44.224 align:middle line:90%


00:39:44.224 --> 00:39:48.390 align:middle line:84%
That was about the last
image I have of him.

00:39:48.390 --> 00:39:51.234 align:middle line:90%


00:39:51.234 --> 00:39:53.140 align:middle line:90%
[CYMBALS CRASH]

00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:56.025 align:middle line:90%
He died soon after that.

00:39:56.025 --> 00:40:07.905 align:middle line:90%


00:40:07.905 --> 00:40:13.350 align:middle line:90%
[DRUMS AND CYMBALS PLAYING]

00:40:13.350 --> 00:40:33.200 align:middle line:90%


00:40:33.200 --> 00:40:35.500 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Without a
doubt, the most remarkable

00:40:35.500 --> 00:40:37.605 align:middle line:84%
part of being a tulku
is the connections

00:40:37.605 --> 00:40:38.405 align:middle line:90%
developed with teachers.

00:40:38.405 --> 00:40:41.830 align:middle line:90%


00:40:41.830 --> 00:40:45.080 align:middle line:84%
In a way, my father was both
my parent and my teacher.

00:40:45.080 --> 00:40:46.195 align:middle line:90%
So losing him was devastating.

00:40:46.195 --> 00:40:50.740 align:middle line:90%


00:40:50.740 --> 00:40:52.280 align:middle line:84%
It's when I'm in
places like this,

00:40:52.280 --> 00:40:54.630 align:middle line:84%
surrounded by our
sacred culture,

00:40:54.630 --> 00:40:55.980 align:middle line:90%
that I feel closest to him.

00:40:55.980 --> 00:41:02.410 align:middle line:90%


00:41:02.410 --> 00:41:05.150 align:middle line:84%
There are only two known
photographs of Shechen Kongtrul

00:41:05.150 --> 00:41:12.190 align:middle line:84%
Rinpoche, one taken in
a Chinese photo studio,

00:41:12.190 --> 00:41:14.850 align:middle line:84%
and the second, from
his later years,

00:41:14.850 --> 00:41:17.810 align:middle line:84%
taken by my teenaged father
with an old box camera

00:41:17.810 --> 00:41:18.980 align:middle line:90%
that he had borrowed.

00:41:18.980 --> 00:41:20.810 align:middle line:84%
He developed and printed
the picture at night

00:41:20.810 --> 00:41:22.760 align:middle line:90%
in the main shrine room.

00:41:22.760 --> 00:41:24.980 align:middle line:84%
I can only imagine how
proud my father must've

00:41:24.980 --> 00:41:27.400 align:middle line:84%
been when he developed
his first picture

00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:29.080 align:middle line:84%
and saw the face of
his teacher appear.

00:41:29.080 --> 00:41:34.514 align:middle line:84%
[TIBETAN HORNS AND CYMBALS
 PLAYING]

00:41:34.514 --> 00:41:53.780 align:middle line:90%


00:41:53.780 --> 00:41:57.200 align:middle line:84%
The entire tulku tradition
began with the second Karmapa,

00:41:57.200 --> 00:41:58.700 align:middle line:90%
more than 700 years ago.

00:41:58.700 --> 00:42:01.550 align:middle line:90%


00:42:01.550 --> 00:42:03.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting on the steps
of Gyuto Monastery.

00:42:03.890 --> 00:42:07.220 align:middle line:84%
We're about to interview
His Holiness, Ogyen Trinley

00:42:07.220 --> 00:42:08.900 align:middle line:90%
Dorje, the 17th Karmapa.

00:42:08.900 --> 00:42:11.840 align:middle line:90%


00:42:11.840 --> 00:42:14.500 align:middle line:84%
The 16th Karmapa
recognized me when

00:42:14.500 --> 00:42:17.950 align:middle line:90%
I was six years old as well.

00:42:17.950 --> 00:42:20.575 align:middle line:84%
So this is the first time I'm
meeting his reincarnation.

00:42:20.575 --> 00:42:24.210 align:middle line:90%


00:42:24.210 --> 00:42:27.960 align:middle line:84%
The current Karmapa is the 17th
in an unbroken line of tulkus.

00:42:27.960 --> 00:42:30.790 align:middle line:90%


00:42:30.790 --> 00:42:34.786 align:middle line:84%
At 14 years old, he made a
daring escape from Tibet.

00:42:34.786 --> 00:42:36.130 align:middle line:84%
Did you have any
problems believing

00:42:36.130 --> 00:42:39.790 align:middle line:84%
that you were a tulku?
-Myself?

00:42:39.790 --> 00:42:40.774 align:middle line:90%
GESAR MUKPO: Yeah, yourself.

00:42:40.774 --> 00:42:47.180 align:middle line:90%


00:42:47.180 --> 00:42:49.580 align:middle line:84%
[SPEAKING TIBETAN WITH
 ASSISTANT]

00:42:49.580 --> 00:44:20.464 align:middle line:90%


00:44:20.464 --> 00:44:23.230 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING AND RINGING BELLS]

00:44:23.230 --> 00:44:24.998 align:middle line:90%


00:44:24.998 --> 00:44:27.020 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: The
Karmapa is an incredibly

00:44:27.020 --> 00:44:30.490 align:middle line:84%
important and beloved figure
in the Tibetan community.

00:44:30.490 --> 00:44:32.940 align:middle line:84%
He is considered a
possible successor

00:44:32.940 --> 00:44:36.130 align:middle line:90%
to the current Dalai Lama.

00:44:36.130 --> 00:44:38.640 align:middle line:84%
Some people have even
said that the Dalai Lama

00:44:38.640 --> 00:44:40.120 align:middle line:90%
is grooming him for this job.

00:44:40.120 --> 00:44:44.485 align:middle line:90%
[RINGING BELLS, CHANTING]

00:44:44.485 --> 00:44:51.780 align:middle line:90%


00:44:51.780 --> 00:44:58.790 align:middle line:84%
Tibetan monasteries, you know,
they're a very big institution.

00:44:58.790 --> 00:45:02.220 align:middle line:90%
They own a lot of properties.

00:45:02.220 --> 00:45:07.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a very big thing in the
social structure in Tibet.

00:45:07.170 --> 00:45:11.570 align:middle line:84%
And wherever there is money,
wherever there's power,

00:45:11.570 --> 00:45:13.720 align:middle line:90%
there's corruption.

00:45:13.720 --> 00:45:16.500 align:middle line:90%
And there's also fear.

00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:20.960 align:middle line:84%
There's also you have
to have management.

00:45:20.960 --> 00:45:21.780 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:45:21.780 --> 00:45:27.400 align:middle line:84%
So it could be for the purpose
of managing a big institution.

00:45:27.400 --> 00:45:34.680 align:middle line:84%
This happens to be an answer
in a society like Tibet.

00:45:34.680 --> 00:45:42.720 align:middle line:10%
I mean, in the West, you elect
the big guy in the White House.

00:45:42.720 --> 00:45:46.160 align:middle line:84%
But it does not really
happen like this is in Tibet.

00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:50.180 align:middle line:90%


00:45:50.180 --> 00:46:00.270 align:middle line:84%
So the way to continue
the big guy in White House

00:46:00.270 --> 00:46:02.600 align:middle line:90%
happens to be like this.

00:46:02.600 --> 00:46:05.990 align:middle line:84%
And it has its charm,
if it is done properly.

00:46:05.990 --> 00:46:07.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, like the
present Dalai Lama,

00:46:07.270 --> 00:46:10.180 align:middle line:84%
he holds one of
the highest throne.

00:46:10.180 --> 00:46:12.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the highest
throne in Tibet.

00:46:12.000 --> 00:46:18.608 align:middle line:84%
And he happens to be a child of
a farmer, really a poor farmer.

00:46:18.608 --> 00:46:23.598 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE GUITAR MUSIC]

00:46:23.598 --> 00:46:56.777 align:middle line:90%


00:46:56.777 --> 00:46:58.110 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: All of
the tulkus that I've

00:46:58.110 --> 00:47:01.580 align:middle line:84%
met have a similar feeling
of almost being lost

00:47:01.580 --> 00:47:04.700 align:middle line:84%
or alone and no one
they can talk to.

00:47:04.700 --> 00:47:07.630 align:middle line:90%
And not really in a bad way.

00:47:07.630 --> 00:47:11.170 align:middle line:84%
Ashoka, he said
to me a one point,

00:47:11.170 --> 00:47:13.110 align:middle line:84%
I don't really think
about this stuff very much

00:47:13.110 --> 00:47:14.070 align:middle line:90%
or talk about it.

00:47:14.070 --> 00:47:18.870 align:middle line:90%


00:47:18.870 --> 00:47:20.950 align:middle line:84%
When you grow up as
a tulku in the West,

00:47:20.950 --> 00:47:23.460 align:middle line:84%
you could sort of completely
flip and not believe it at all

00:47:23.460 --> 00:47:25.330 align:middle line:90%
or completely believe it.

00:47:25.330 --> 00:47:28.910 align:middle line:84%
And it can flip back and
forth with one thought.

00:47:28.910 --> 00:47:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And I really see Wyatt
going through that.

00:47:30.530 --> 00:47:33.190 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting for me to
realize-- because I'm 34 now

00:47:33.190 --> 00:47:36.250 align:middle line:84%
and Wyatt is 20-- that
he's actually looking

00:47:36.250 --> 00:47:41.450 align:middle line:84%
to me for advice or to ask
me what I've gone through

00:47:41.450 --> 00:47:43.720 align:middle line:84%
and how I've dealt with it,
and realize that actually I

00:47:43.720 --> 00:47:45.360 align:middle line:84%
have some kind of
valuable experience

00:47:45.360 --> 00:47:47.530 align:middle line:90%
that I can reassure him with.

00:47:47.530 --> 00:47:50.100 align:middle line:90%


00:47:50.100 --> 00:47:53.800 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've always struggled
with this kind of stuff.

00:47:53.800 --> 00:47:57.990 align:middle line:84%
The whole idea of being a
tulku is so sort of far-fetched

00:47:57.990 --> 00:48:00.850 align:middle line:84%
and so out there that if
you tell it to most people,

00:48:00.850 --> 00:48:04.010 align:middle line:84%
they just think it's some
complete mumbo-jumbo bullshit.

00:48:04.010 --> 00:48:05.040 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:48:05.040 --> 00:48:07.690 align:middle line:84%
I think the idea of
tulku is all right.

00:48:07.690 --> 00:48:11.560 align:middle line:84%
It's just when you
give someone a title.

00:48:11.560 --> 00:48:15.190 align:middle line:84%
And what-- you said
something earlier like,

00:48:15.190 --> 00:48:18.130 align:middle line:84%
you tell someone they're
supposed to be this person.

00:48:18.130 --> 00:48:19.330 align:middle line:84%
Like, does that
mean you're supposed

00:48:19.330 --> 00:48:20.670 align:middle line:90%
to act like that person?

00:48:20.670 --> 00:48:22.410 align:middle line:84%
Does that mean you're
supposed to carry on whatever

00:48:22.410 --> 00:48:24.340 align:middle line:90%
that person was doing?

00:48:24.340 --> 00:48:26.420 align:middle line:84%
Is that person
different than you?

00:48:26.420 --> 00:48:27.290 align:middle line:90%
How much--

00:48:27.290 --> 00:48:31.026 align:middle line:90%


00:48:31.026 --> 00:48:33.200 align:middle line:90%
It's just so strange, man.

00:48:33.200 --> 00:48:39.040 align:middle line:90%
[BUS ENGINE ROARING]

00:48:39.040 --> 00:48:40.406 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you believe
in reincarnation,

00:48:40.406 --> 00:48:46.380 align:middle line:84%
then everybody's
a tulku, you know.

00:48:46.380 --> 00:48:51.400 align:middle line:84%
But the tulkus that are
recognized are supposed to be,

00:48:51.400 --> 00:48:53.450 align:middle line:84%
what is it, and
eighth-level bodhisattva,

00:48:53.450 --> 00:49:01.880 align:middle line:84%
who has power over karma, power
over rebirth, power over like,

00:49:01.880 --> 00:49:08.210 align:middle line:84%
time, like they
can completely defy

00:49:08.210 --> 00:49:16.000 align:middle line:84%
all the laws of physical
science because they're mind

00:49:16.000 --> 00:49:26.810 align:middle line:90%
is so great, so precise.

00:49:26.810 --> 00:49:31.800 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I guess that is really
been my experience is that I

00:49:31.800 --> 00:49:34.960 align:middle line:84%
try to not think about
it in those terms

00:49:34.960 --> 00:49:39.186 align:middle line:84%
because that's just
to unbelievable.

00:49:39.186 --> 00:49:41.890 align:middle line:84%
I try to understand it
on a more personal level.

00:49:41.890 --> 00:49:45.311 align:middle line:90%


00:49:45.311 --> 00:49:46.010 align:middle line:90%
To try?

00:49:46.010 --> 00:49:48.440 align:middle line:84%
I guess I feel like when I
read about that kind of stuff,

00:49:48.440 --> 00:49:50.420 align:middle line:84%
it makes more sense
to me because it's

00:49:50.420 --> 00:49:54.150 align:middle line:84%
not just some like
vague concept,

00:49:54.150 --> 00:49:56.700 align:middle line:90%
like, there's an actual design.

00:49:56.700 --> 00:49:59.470 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole design to the
way it works, just like there's

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:02.290 align:middle line:84%
a whole design into
the way the tree grows,

00:50:02.290 --> 00:50:12.490 align:middle line:84%
like there's certain causes that
actually have formed the tulku.

00:50:12.490 --> 00:50:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And like it's a very
important thing.

00:50:15.920 --> 00:50:17.840 align:middle line:90%
It's really important.

00:50:17.840 --> 00:50:22.710 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm curious
to know is is it

00:50:22.710 --> 00:50:26.710 align:middle line:84%
right to keep this
tradition going in the West

00:50:26.710 --> 00:50:30.460 align:middle line:84%
when there's no system for it to
be held, like there's no system

00:50:30.460 --> 00:50:32.150 align:middle line:90%
to bring up the tulku.

00:50:32.150 --> 00:50:33.480 align:middle line:84%
And there's no
parents that are just

00:50:33.480 --> 00:50:34.860 align:middle line:90%
going to give up their kid.

00:50:34.860 --> 00:50:36.026 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's
no way someone who

00:50:36.026 --> 00:50:37.859 align:middle line:84%
is born in the West is just
going to hop into a Tibetan

00:50:37.859 --> 00:50:42.270 align:middle line:90%
shedra and study 14 years.

00:50:42.270 --> 00:50:43.890 align:middle line:90%
It's almost impossible.

00:50:43.890 --> 00:50:47.092 align:middle line:84%
WYATT ARNOLD: Yeah, I figured
that out actually. [LAUGHS]

00:50:47.092 --> 00:50:50.960 align:middle line:84%
Hello, could we get
two chai, please?

00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:55.935 align:middle line:84%
Trying to have a strong
grip on a so-called culture

00:50:55.935 --> 00:51:00.940 align:middle line:84%
and tradition in many
ways is not a wise thing.

00:51:00.940 --> 00:51:03.960 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism has to transcend
culture and tradition.

00:51:03.960 --> 00:51:05.020 align:middle line:90%
You know all of that.

00:51:05.020 --> 00:51:08.040 align:middle line:90%


00:51:08.040 --> 00:51:13.380 align:middle line:84%
But of course, we have
to do it carefully

00:51:13.380 --> 00:51:17.060 align:middle line:84%
because cultures and
traditions are like the means.

00:51:17.060 --> 00:51:18.590 align:middle line:90%
It's like the medium.

00:51:18.590 --> 00:51:25.260 align:middle line:84%
So we don't want to also sort
of just toss it out overnight.

00:51:25.260 --> 00:51:31.860 align:middle line:84%
It has to slowly,
organically change.

00:51:31.860 --> 00:51:32.860 align:middle line:90%
And it will change.

00:51:32.860 --> 00:51:34.680 align:middle line:90%
It has to.

00:51:34.680 --> 00:51:37.140 align:middle line:84%
Buddha said, all compounded
things are impermanent.

00:51:37.140 --> 00:51:38.550 align:middle line:90%
It will change.

00:51:38.550 --> 00:51:42.660 align:middle line:84%
And thanks to the Western
cynicism, skepticism,

00:51:42.660 --> 00:51:43.622 align:middle line:90%
this is good.

00:51:43.622 --> 00:51:46.990 align:middle line:90%


00:51:46.990 --> 00:51:53.730 align:middle line:84%
This quest and this
habit and this arrogance

00:51:53.730 --> 00:51:57.390 align:middle line:84%
or pride of wanting
to be objective

00:51:57.390 --> 00:52:02.140 align:middle line:90%
ironically helps Buddhism.

00:52:02.140 --> 00:52:03.470 align:middle line:90%
Because when Buddhism travels--

00:52:03.470 --> 00:52:04.315 align:middle line:90%
I mean, there are.

00:52:04.315 --> 00:52:08.510 align:middle line:84%
There's a small
pocket of completely

00:52:08.510 --> 00:52:13.940 align:middle line:84%
wishy-washy, mumbo-jumbo,
feeling this, vision that.

00:52:13.940 --> 00:52:15.000 align:middle line:90%
You understand?

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:20.100 align:middle line:84%
But there's also great
many Western Buddhists

00:52:20.100 --> 00:52:24.930 align:middle line:84%
really going to Buddhism
because there is a reason

00:52:24.930 --> 00:52:28.460 align:middle line:84%
and because it's
a reason-oriented,

00:52:28.460 --> 00:52:30.320 align:middle line:90%
logic-oriented path.

00:52:30.320 --> 00:52:31.530 align:middle line:90%
And this is good.

00:52:31.530 --> 00:52:32.545 align:middle line:90%
This will be our guarantee.

00:52:32.545 --> 00:52:41.310 align:middle line:90%


00:52:41.310 --> 00:52:43.457 align:middle line:84%
I have the biggest fear
that I'll meet someone.

00:52:43.457 --> 00:52:44.590 align:middle line:84%
And then they'll
know I'm a tulku,

00:52:44.590 --> 00:52:46.880 align:middle line:84%
and then they'll turn
around and they'll be like,

00:52:46.880 --> 00:52:48.090 align:middle line:90%
he's not a tulku.

00:52:48.090 --> 00:52:50.990 align:middle line:90%
You got to be kidding me.

00:52:50.990 --> 00:53:00.030 align:middle line:84%
Because I have this huge
welling of pride in that.

00:53:00.030 --> 00:53:03.610 align:middle line:90%
And then that's cut down.

00:53:03.610 --> 00:53:09.070 align:middle line:84%
Then I feel like I'm come
nothing, which sucks.

00:53:09.070 --> 00:53:13.157 align:middle line:84%
Like, I just want
to be a normal guy.

00:53:13.157 --> 00:53:13.890 align:middle line:90%
Well, you are though.

00:53:13.890 --> 00:53:16.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:53:16.320 --> 00:53:17.950 align:middle line:90%
But not really.

00:53:17.950 --> 00:53:19.200 align:middle line:90%
Are you sure?

00:53:19.200 --> 00:53:22.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, I mean if
Chagdud Tulku was right.

00:53:22.480 --> 00:53:25.330 align:middle line:90%


00:53:25.330 --> 00:53:29.440 align:middle line:84%
And even if it's not true,
there's still the title there.

00:53:29.440 --> 00:53:31.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it sounds
like it's better to me

00:53:31.720 --> 00:53:38.160 align:middle line:84%
to just stop recognizing,
stop giving titles and thrones

00:53:38.160 --> 00:53:41.560 align:middle line:84%
in the West because as
soon as you do that,

00:53:41.560 --> 00:53:47.225 align:middle line:84%
it just becomes political,
like this whole social ladder.

00:53:47.225 --> 00:53:49.300 align:middle line:90%
And you're here on it.

00:53:49.300 --> 00:53:51.300 align:middle line:90%
And everybody looks up to you.

00:53:51.300 --> 00:53:54.100 align:middle line:84%
But you have this horrible,
overwhelming sense

00:53:54.100 --> 00:53:55.830 align:middle line:90%
of self-doubt.

00:53:55.830 --> 00:53:58.260 align:middle line:90%
Yet you love being up there.

00:53:58.260 --> 00:54:00.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's what I'm going
through a lot now is just

00:54:00.480 --> 00:54:02.310 align:middle line:84%
trying to like let go
of these expectations,

00:54:02.310 --> 00:54:08.860 align:middle line:84%
let go of my doubt, let go of
my feelings of fear and guilt,

00:54:08.860 --> 00:54:11.910 align:middle line:84%
and realize that
those are totally

00:54:11.910 --> 00:54:15.780 align:middle line:84%
associated with my perception
of how other people see me.

00:54:15.780 --> 00:54:18.060 align:middle line:84%
I got a lot of
everything from my dad,

00:54:18.060 --> 00:54:22.923 align:middle line:84%
too, because he's really
intense about this whole thing.

00:54:22.923 --> 00:54:27.580 align:middle line:84%
Like, he's got big
ideas, big ideas.

00:54:27.580 --> 00:54:29.680 align:middle line:84%
And when you're a
teenager and you're

00:54:29.680 --> 00:54:35.230 align:middle line:84%
not too cool with your dad,
you're trying to be rebel.

00:54:35.230 --> 00:54:37.020 align:middle line:90%
It just makes it all worse.

00:54:37.020 --> 00:54:39.658 align:middle line:84%
At least, it made it
so much worse for me.

00:54:39.658 --> 00:54:44.090 align:middle line:90%


00:54:44.090 --> 00:54:45.660 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:54:45.660 --> 00:54:49.960 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when your father
passed away, did you feel lost?

00:54:49.960 --> 00:54:51.720 align:middle line:84%
Looking back now,
I just realize

00:54:51.720 --> 00:54:54.640 align:middle line:84%
that my dad had complete
faith that I'd figure it out.

00:54:54.640 --> 00:54:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And what all he needed to do was
like give me his lesson of what

00:54:58.160 --> 00:54:59.986 align:middle line:84%
it meant to be a
good human being,

00:54:59.986 --> 00:55:02.991 align:middle line:84%
and that I would
figure things out,

00:55:02.991 --> 00:55:04.590 align:middle line:84%
everything I need to
figure out, if I could just

00:55:04.590 --> 00:55:11.611 align:middle line:84%
work from the basis of making
my life healthy in some way

00:55:11.611 --> 00:55:12.535 align:middle line:90%
and being sane.

00:55:12.535 --> 00:55:14.320 align:middle line:90%


00:55:14.320 --> 00:55:16.350 align:middle line:90%
MAN: Lights out.

00:55:16.350 --> 00:55:17.090 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:55:17.090 --> 00:55:18.554 align:middle line:90%
I have--

00:55:18.554 --> 00:55:20.018 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Will you
sell me the onion?

00:55:20.018 --> 00:55:20.994 align:middle line:90%
MAN: No.

00:55:20.994 --> 00:55:22.650 align:middle line:90%
It is enough when you put--

00:55:22.650 --> 00:55:24.862 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: It's a
very Tibetan onion.

00:55:24.862 --> 00:55:27.808 align:middle line:84%
I think you're going to
have to turn this over.

00:55:27.808 --> 00:55:28.790 align:middle line:90%
Turn it.

00:55:28.790 --> 00:55:30.754 align:middle line:84%
WYATT ARNOLD: Yeah,
and get these-- No?

00:55:30.754 --> 00:55:32.718 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTING]

00:55:32.718 --> 00:55:34.682 align:middle line:90%


00:55:34.682 --> 00:55:40.083 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE SONG PLAYING]

00:55:40.083 --> 00:55:48.761 align:middle line:90%


00:55:48.761 --> 00:55:49.460 align:middle line:90%
It's delicious.

00:55:49.460 --> 00:55:52.750 align:middle line:90%


00:55:52.750 --> 00:55:55.000 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: How do you say
"it's delicious" in Tibetan?

00:55:55.000 --> 00:55:58.998 align:middle line:90%
[BOTH SPEAKING TIBETAN]

00:55:58.998 --> 00:56:04.476 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE SONG CONTINUES]

00:56:04.476 --> 00:57:28.820 align:middle line:90%


00:57:28.820 --> 00:57:31.860 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: When I was
15, my father passed away.

00:57:31.860 --> 00:57:34.760 align:middle line:84%
And my mother decided it was
time to send me to Nepal.

00:57:34.760 --> 00:57:37.620 align:middle line:84%
She plucked me out of school
and put me in the hands of Dilgo

00:57:37.620 --> 00:57:40.330 align:middle line:84%
Khyentse Rinpoche,
the Tibetan lama had

00:57:40.330 --> 00:57:41.865 align:middle line:90%
recognized and enthroned me.

00:57:41.865 --> 00:57:51.860 align:middle line:90%


00:57:51.860 --> 00:57:55.046 align:middle line:84%
It's been almost 19 years
since I've been back to Nepal.

00:57:55.046 --> 00:58:00.006 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE SONG CONTINUES]

00:58:00.006 --> 00:58:17.366 align:middle line:90%


00:58:17.366 --> 00:58:19.350 align:middle line:90%
I hope no one recognizes me.

00:58:19.350 --> 00:58:34.726 align:middle line:90%


00:58:34.726 --> 00:58:37.650 align:middle line:90%
[PRAYER WHEELS SQUEAK]

00:58:37.650 --> 00:58:38.750 align:middle line:90%
What do these things do?

00:58:38.750 --> 00:58:47.910 align:middle line:90%


00:58:47.910 --> 00:58:51.110 align:middle line:84%
This is also-- obviously, since
Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche was

00:58:51.110 --> 00:58:52.350 align:middle line:84%
here, this is the
first place that I

00:58:52.350 --> 00:58:57.325 align:middle line:84%
actually spent any extended
period of time with him.

00:58:57.325 --> 00:59:01.470 align:middle line:90%
And he was an amazing person.

00:59:01.470 --> 00:59:03.160 align:middle line:90%
He just-- he changed my life.

00:59:03.160 --> 00:59:08.450 align:middle line:90%


00:59:08.450 --> 00:59:16.230 align:middle line:84%
When I first came here, I met
Rabjam Rinpoche, who's the head

00:59:16.230 --> 00:59:18.520 align:middle line:90%
of this monastery, pretty much.

00:59:18.520 --> 00:59:21.780 align:middle line:84%
And he knew I was just
coming over from the West.

00:59:21.780 --> 00:59:23.810 align:middle line:90%
I was 15 years old.

00:59:23.810 --> 00:59:26.040 align:middle line:84%
So he had his television
brought down to my house

00:59:26.040 --> 00:59:27.080 align:middle line:90%
and a bunch of videotapes.

00:59:27.080 --> 00:59:30.440 align:middle line:10%
And for the first three days, I
just watched movies constantly.

00:59:30.440 --> 00:59:33.430 align:middle line:10%
And I came back on the fourth
day and the VCR and television

00:59:33.430 --> 00:59:35.100 align:middle line:10%
were gone.

00:59:35.100 --> 00:59:38.060 align:middle line:10%
And that's when I
started studying Tibetan.

00:59:38.060 --> 00:59:41.532 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

00:59:41.532 --> 00:59:46.988 align:middle line:90%
[GENTLE SONG PLAYS]

00:59:46.988 --> 01:00:12.820 align:middle line:90%


01:00:12.820 --> 01:00:15.955 align:middle line:84%
First of all, I was born in
a Buddhist family, really,

01:00:15.955 --> 01:00:18.140 align:middle line:90%
like big lamas here and there.

01:00:18.140 --> 01:00:20.410 align:middle line:84%
And then at the age
of like, really young,

01:00:20.410 --> 01:00:22.965 align:middle line:90%
I was basically shoved into.

01:00:22.965 --> 01:00:25.750 align:middle line:90%


01:00:25.750 --> 01:00:28.580 align:middle line:90%
I will not use the word "force."

01:00:28.580 --> 01:00:30.460 align:middle line:90%
But just basically.

01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:33.535 align:middle line:90%
So there was no reference.

01:00:33.535 --> 01:00:36.320 align:middle line:90%
There's no reference.

01:00:36.320 --> 01:00:37.677 align:middle line:90%
This is all changed now.

01:00:37.677 --> 01:00:41.160 align:middle line:90%


01:00:41.160 --> 01:00:43.110 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Shortly
after arriving in Nepal,

01:00:43.110 --> 01:00:45.192 align:middle line:90%
I met Reuben Derkson.

01:00:45.192 --> 01:00:50.030 align:middle line:84%
Born in Amsterdam in 1986,
raised in Nepal and Bhutan,

01:00:50.030 --> 01:00:53.430 align:middle line:84%
Reuben was recognized as a
tulku when he was 11 years old.

01:00:53.430 --> 01:01:00.340 align:middle line:90%


01:01:00.340 --> 01:01:01.970 align:middle line:84%
REUBEN DERKSON:
When I was young,

01:01:01.970 --> 01:01:04.910 align:middle line:84%
I had memories of
the previous life.

01:01:04.910 --> 01:01:08.100 align:middle line:84%
And so my mother was writing
those down and kind of keeping

01:01:08.100 --> 01:01:10.180 align:middle line:90%
a journal of what I was saying.

01:01:10.180 --> 01:01:15.850 align:middle line:84%
And I described the
monastery that I grew up in

01:01:15.850 --> 01:01:18.000 align:middle line:84%
or that I taught in
in my previous life,

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:20.880 align:middle line:84%
and some of the
events that went on.

01:01:20.880 --> 01:01:24.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I have no memory
of this whatsoever now.

01:01:24.330 --> 01:01:28.990 align:middle line:84%
But so they had two
Tibetan monk friends,

01:01:28.990 --> 01:01:31.160 align:middle line:90%
or Bhutanese monk friends.

01:01:31.160 --> 01:01:34.250 align:middle line:84%
And they said it was a
big deal or something.

01:01:34.250 --> 01:01:40.210 align:middle line:84%
And when Dilgo Khyentse Rinpoche
was being coronated here,

01:01:40.210 --> 01:01:42.930 align:middle line:84%
I was also recognized
at that time.

01:01:42.930 --> 01:01:45.390 align:middle line:84%
So I finished my
school year at Lincoln,

01:01:45.390 --> 01:01:48.210 align:middle line:84%
which is the American
school here in Kathmandu.

01:01:48.210 --> 01:01:50.455 align:middle line:84%
And then I went
to the monastery.

01:01:50.455 --> 01:01:53.510 align:middle line:90%


01:01:53.510 --> 01:01:55.810 align:middle line:84%
I can say it wasn't
completely voluntary

01:01:55.810 --> 01:01:59.560 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't really know
what I was getting into.

01:01:59.560 --> 01:02:01.970 align:middle line:84%
But I was also OK with going
into the whole Buddhist thing

01:02:01.970 --> 01:02:06.080 align:middle line:84%
because I had an image
of these Buddhist monks

01:02:06.080 --> 01:02:10.020 align:middle line:84%
as being holy and serene
and all-knowing and wise,

01:02:10.020 --> 01:02:14.860 align:middle line:84%
and that they could really
teach me the whole Buddhist

01:02:14.860 --> 01:02:17.060 align:middle line:90%
philosophy and everything.

01:02:17.060 --> 01:02:18.460 align:middle line:90%
Six days a week, five days?

01:02:18.460 --> 01:02:19.982 align:middle line:84%
Six days a week, yeah.
Sunday was off.

01:02:19.982 --> 01:02:23.820 align:middle line:84%
I can imagine three years
of that kind of intensity

01:02:23.820 --> 01:02:29.120 align:middle line:84%
for anyone is asking
a lot of someone

01:02:29.120 --> 01:02:32.460 align:middle line:84%
to be able to take, let alone a
young child who hadn't grown up

01:02:32.460 --> 01:02:34.540 align:middle line:90%
in this kind of surroundings.

01:02:34.540 --> 01:02:38.340 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, most people have no idea
what goes down in a monastery.

01:02:38.340 --> 01:02:41.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you put
600 men together,

01:02:41.810 --> 01:02:43.950 align:middle line:84%
what do you expect
you're going to get?

01:02:43.950 --> 01:02:46.140 align:middle line:84%
There are some people
in the monastery who

01:02:46.140 --> 01:02:49.050 align:middle line:84%
were good leaders,
who were practicing

01:02:49.050 --> 01:02:53.270 align:middle line:84%
every day, who really were
people you could look up to.

01:02:53.270 --> 01:02:58.600 align:middle line:84%
However, the majority of
the cases, the monster

01:02:58.600 --> 01:03:03.300 align:middle line:84%
there was basically a cesspool
of jealousy, of gossip,

01:03:03.300 --> 01:03:12.310 align:middle line:84%
of hate, of violence, and very
un-Buddhist in a lot of ways,

01:03:12.310 --> 01:03:14.070 align:middle line:84%
at least, un-Buddhist
in the sense

01:03:14.070 --> 01:03:16.800 align:middle line:84%
that the preach one thing,
and then they turn around

01:03:16.800 --> 01:03:19.330 align:middle line:90%
and do exactly the opposite.

01:03:19.330 --> 01:03:21.010 align:middle line:84%
Anything you find,
you would have found

01:03:21.010 --> 01:03:25.390 align:middle line:84%
in a Christian monastery, from
homosexuality to child abuse

01:03:25.390 --> 01:03:27.650 align:middle line:90%
to beatings.

01:03:27.650 --> 01:03:29.967 align:middle line:84%
That's something that
Dzongsar Rinpoche was saying

01:03:29.967 --> 01:03:31.300 align:middle line:84%
when this person asked
him this question

01:03:31.300 --> 01:03:34.740 align:middle line:90%
about Bhutan and Sri Lanka.

01:03:34.740 --> 01:03:38.230 align:middle line:84%
Like, there's a difference
between Buddhism and Buddhists.

01:03:38.230 --> 01:03:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And you'd better
recognize that there's

01:03:39.560 --> 01:03:41.559 align:middle line:84%
a difference between them, or
else you won't be able to make

01:03:41.559 --> 01:03:42.440 align:middle line:90%
any sense out of it.

01:03:42.440 --> 01:03:46.620 align:middle line:84%
Just because someone's
studying Buddhism

01:03:46.620 --> 01:03:49.630 align:middle line:84%
does not mean that they
represent the values

01:03:49.630 --> 01:03:52.220 align:middle line:90%
of what it talks about.

01:03:52.220 --> 01:03:54.060 align:middle line:84%
Do you consider yourself
a Buddhist still?

01:03:54.060 --> 01:03:56.580 align:middle line:90%
No.

01:03:56.580 --> 01:03:58.550 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Now, yet
still, as you told me,

01:03:58.550 --> 01:04:01.020 align:middle line:90%
you will go back to Bhutan.

01:04:01.020 --> 01:04:05.750 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, there is a ceremony that
lasts about a week in Bhutan.

01:04:05.750 --> 01:04:09.180 align:middle line:84%
And I have been going back there
every year for the one week

01:04:09.180 --> 01:04:13.250 align:middle line:90%
to MC the ceremony.

01:04:13.250 --> 01:04:16.340 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, the reason
I do that-- see,

01:04:16.340 --> 01:04:19.420 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if I
believe in reincarnation

01:04:19.420 --> 01:04:24.140 align:middle line:84%
or in all the Buddhist values,
the traditional values.

01:04:24.140 --> 01:04:25.310 align:middle line:90%
I really don't.

01:04:25.310 --> 01:04:28.140 align:middle line:84%
But the reason I go
back there is not

01:04:28.140 --> 01:04:30.900 align:middle line:84%
because I, say, want to
go back there every year,

01:04:30.900 --> 01:04:34.145 align:middle line:84%
but more because it makes these
people so incredibly happy.

01:04:34.145 --> 01:04:47.162 align:middle line:90%


01:04:47.162 --> 01:04:48.695 align:middle line:84%
DZONGSAR KHYENTSE RINPOCHE:
In Buddhism, there

01:04:48.695 --> 01:04:51.350 align:middle line:84%
is concepts such as
reincarnation, concepts

01:04:51.350 --> 01:04:54.390 align:middle line:90%
such as tulku, all of that.

01:04:54.390 --> 01:05:01.580 align:middle line:84%
But the institutionalized tulku
system that we have in Tibetan,

01:05:01.580 --> 01:05:03.320 align:middle line:84%
I don't think
something like this

01:05:03.320 --> 01:05:07.790 align:middle line:90%
exists originally in Buddhism.

01:05:07.790 --> 01:05:10.740 align:middle line:84%
In the sutras and the
shastras, we never hear.

01:05:10.740 --> 01:05:14.680 align:middle line:84%
We never read about
Kashyapa's or Maudgalyayana's

01:05:14.680 --> 01:05:15.740 align:middle line:90%
or Shariputra has died.

01:05:15.740 --> 01:05:17.750 align:middle line:84%
And then a bunch
of guys are trying

01:05:17.750 --> 01:05:19.100 align:middle line:90%
to find their reincarnation.

01:05:19.100 --> 01:05:21.670 align:middle line:90%


01:05:21.670 --> 01:05:23.470 align:middle line:84%
We don't know this
kind of event.

01:05:23.470 --> 01:05:31.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are, OK, mentions
of Ashvaghosha, [INAUDIBLE]

01:05:31.010 --> 01:05:32.180 align:middle line:90%
who reincarnates.

01:05:32.180 --> 01:05:35.434 align:middle line:90%


01:05:35.434 --> 01:05:36.340 align:middle line:90%
You understand.

01:05:36.340 --> 01:05:42.040 align:middle line:84%
But the actual institution or
the culture or the tradition

01:05:42.040 --> 01:05:48.900 align:middle line:84%
of trying to find a tulku
and then enthroning them

01:05:48.900 --> 01:05:52.640 align:middle line:84%
and all of that is a
bit of a Tibetan thing.

01:05:52.640 --> 01:05:56.690 align:middle line:90%
Started much later, I feel.

01:05:56.690 --> 01:06:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And now, I personally
think that to hold

01:06:00.310 --> 01:06:06.000 align:middle line:84%
that culture, institutionalized
tulku, that culture is dying.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:07.340 align:middle line:90%
It's not going to work anymore.

01:06:07.340 --> 01:06:09.970 align:middle line:90%


01:06:09.970 --> 01:06:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And if it doesn't work, I think
that's almost for the better

01:06:13.390 --> 01:06:19.750 align:middle line:84%
because this tulku is going
to-- if the Tibetans are

01:06:19.750 --> 01:06:24.460 align:middle line:84%
not careful, this tulku system
is going to ruin Buddhism.

01:06:24.460 --> 01:06:26.100 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the
day, Buddhism is more

01:06:26.100 --> 01:06:27.600 align:middle line:90%
important than tulku system.

01:06:27.600 --> 01:06:32.050 align:middle line:84%
Who cares about tulku
and what happens to them?

01:06:32.050 --> 01:06:32.920 align:middle line:90%
So I just dial?

01:06:32.920 --> 01:06:34.680 align:middle line:90%
WYATT ARNOLD: Yeah.

01:06:34.680 --> 01:06:35.740 align:middle line:90%
Zero, zero, one?

01:06:35.740 --> 01:06:36.718 align:middle line:90%
WYATT ARNOLD: Only one.

