Hello?

01:08:06.972 --> 01:08:09.290 align:middle line:90%
GIRL: Can you say something?

01:08:09.290 --> 01:08:11.038 align:middle line:90%
Hello.

01:08:11.038 --> 01:08:11.994 align:middle line:90%
Hello, hello.

01:08:11.994 --> 01:08:19.960 align:middle line:90%


01:08:19.960 --> 01:08:22.079 align:middle line:90%
[BEEP]

01:08:22.079 --> 01:08:26.869 align:middle line:90%
[SONG CONTINUES]

01:08:26.869 --> 01:09:25.057 align:middle line:90%


01:09:25.057 --> 01:09:26.390 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: I'm proud
of being a tulku.

01:09:26.390 --> 01:09:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And despite my questions, it's
something very special and dear

01:09:30.370 --> 01:09:31.899 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

01:09:31.899 --> 01:09:35.910 align:middle line:84%
And I wouldn't change anything
about this precious experience.

01:09:35.910 --> 01:09:38.130 align:middle line:84%
I value the connection
to my teachers,

01:09:38.130 --> 01:09:40.776 align:middle line:84%
the Tibetan community,
and my monastery.

01:09:40.776 --> 01:09:46.144 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS PLAYING]

01:09:46.144 --> 01:09:52.976 align:middle line:90%


01:09:52.976 --> 01:09:58.832 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

01:09:58.832 --> 01:10:02.310 align:middle line:90%


01:10:02.310 --> 01:10:03.540 align:middle line:90%
Hello, Rinpoche.

01:10:03.540 --> 01:10:04.590 align:middle line:90%
Ah, so sorry.

01:10:04.590 --> 01:10:06.765 align:middle line:90%
I didn't recognize you. [LAUGHS]

01:10:06.765 --> 01:10:09.060 align:middle line:84%
Welcome back.
I'm glad you made it.

01:10:09.060 --> 01:10:10.640 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't sure if
you would be here.

01:10:10.640 --> 01:10:13.460 align:middle line:84%
When I first came to
Shechen Monastery in Nepal,

01:10:13.460 --> 01:10:15.200 align:middle line:84%
the young abbot,
Rabjung Rinpoche,

01:10:15.200 --> 01:10:18.390 align:middle line:84%
helped me make the
difficult transition.

01:10:18.390 --> 01:10:20.870 align:middle line:84%
His kind heart and jovial
nature made me feel

01:10:20.870 --> 01:10:22.290 align:middle line:90%
at ease a world away from home.

01:10:22.290 --> 01:10:35.290 align:middle line:90%


01:10:35.290 --> 01:10:38.830 align:middle line:84%
At 16, after spending a
year in the monastery,

01:10:38.830 --> 01:10:41.400 align:middle line:84%
I was feeling homesick and
decided I didn't want to be

01:10:41.400 --> 01:10:43.260 align:middle line:90%
there for the rest of my life.

01:10:43.260 --> 01:10:44.660 align:middle line:90%
I called my mother.

01:10:44.660 --> 01:10:48.440 align:middle line:84%
And she arranged for me
to come back immediately.

01:10:48.440 --> 01:10:51.487 align:middle line:84%
I've often wondered if I
made the right decision.

01:10:51.487 --> 01:10:55.383 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING TIBETAN]

01:10:55.383 --> 01:11:06.019 align:middle line:90%


01:11:06.019 --> 01:11:08.119 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: Including everyone
here, how many monks are there?

01:11:08.119 --> 01:11:09.077 align:middle line:90%
MAN 2: Almost 300.

01:11:09.077 --> 01:11:10.514 align:middle line:90%
GESAR MUKPO: Wow.

01:11:10.514 --> 01:11:16.750 align:middle line:84%
MAN 2: But some are like out in
retreat or they're [INAUDIBLE].

01:11:16.750 --> 01:11:18.870 align:middle line:84%
GESAR MUKPO: So most
people here in the shedra?

01:11:18.870 --> 01:11:20.430 align:middle line:84%
MAN 2: Shedra and
[INAUDIBLE] school.

01:11:20.430 --> 01:11:27.060 align:middle line:90%


01:11:27.060 --> 01:11:30.993 align:middle line:90%
[SIGHS]

01:11:30.993 --> 01:11:44.690 align:middle line:90%


01:11:44.690 --> 01:11:49.597 align:middle line:90%
[TIBETAN HORNS AND CYMBALS PLAY]

01:11:49.597 --> 01:11:53.950 align:middle line:90%


01:11:53.950 --> 01:11:58.120 align:middle line:84%
Whether I am a tulku or
not is insignificant.

01:11:58.120 --> 01:12:00.280 align:middle line:84%
I have a tremendous
connection to this monastery

01:12:00.280 --> 01:12:04.230 align:middle line:84%
